liked_videos.title: How Tesla Became The Most Popular Car Brand In Norway
liked_videos.description:
Norway has had massive success with EV adoption, with 82% of new cars sold in the country last year being electric. This high adoption rate can be attributed to the generous subsidies that Norway has offered to electric vehicle owners as well as the country‚Äôs investment in charging infrastructure. Tesla‚Äôs sales in Norway represent only a sliver of the 1.8 million vehicles the company delivered last year, but Norway‚Äôs importance to Tesla goes beyond cold hard cash. Tesla‚Äôs early foothold in the country has made Norway the perfect proving ground for the company and acted as a poster child for the EV transition as a whole. As a result, Tesla CEO, Elon Musk has taken a number of trips to the small Nordic country and has often praised Norway‚Äôs support of electric vehicles. Norwegians were the first European customers to receive deliveries of the Model S in 2013 and it quickly became the country‚Äôs best-selling car. Today, that title has been transferred over to Tesla‚Äôs Model Y. But with competition from other EV cars from automakers including Toyota, Skoda, Volkswagan and BYD heating up, it remains to be seen if Norwegians will continue to choose Tesla in the future. To learn more about Norway‚Äôs success with electric vehicle adoption, check out CNBC‚Äôs documentary: https://youtu.be/R5DbRyeZNRk

liked_videos.title: What the Red Sea ship attacks are really about
liked_videos.description:
Yemen's Houthis say they're avenging Gaza. But there's a lot more to it.

Help keep Vox free for everybody: http://www.vox.com/give-now 

After the Israel-Hamas war broke out on October 7, 2023, the Houthis, a Yemeni rebel group, began attacking ships passing through the Red Sea. The Houthis pledged to attack any ship in these waters that does business with Israel, to protest Israel‚Äôs war on Gaza and to show solidarity with Palestinians there. But as the attacks have continued, another motive for them has become apparent: strengthening the Houthis‚Äô control of Yemen. 

After a nine-year civil war, the Houthis today control a sizable area in Yemen, with over 70 percent of the Yemeni population within the group‚Äôs territory. The conflict has devastated the country, creating one of the worst humanitarian crises in the world. More than 377,000 Yemenis have been killed ‚Äî by airstrikes from a Saudi-led coalition; landmines and detonations planted by the Houthis; a lack of medical services; and scarcity of food and water due to a naval blockade. And both the Saudi-led coalition and the Houthis have been accused of committing war crimes against Yemenis.

Today, the Houthis are attempting to establish themselves as Yemen's legitimate leaders in the eyes of Yemenis, though they‚Äôve done little to improve the country‚Äôs humanitarian crisis. The Red Sea attacks, which appear to have significant support among the Yemeni people, might be a means to achieve that goal.

Subscribe to our channel and turn on notifications (üîî) so you don't miss any videos: http://goo.gl/0bsAjO

liked_videos.title: Volkswagen will bring POLO in some form soon! - Brand Director, Ashish Gupta
liked_videos.description:
I had the privilege of conducting an insightful interview with Mr. Ashish Gupta at the highly anticipated VW Annual Brand Conference 2024. During our discussion, we delved into various aspects of Volkswagen's innovative ventures and strategic initiatives.

One highlight of our conversation was the unveiling of Polo, Volkswagen's latest electric vehicle. Mr. Gupta provided valuable insights into the development process, highlighting its significance in the company's commitment to sustainability and technological advancement.

Additionally, we explored Volkswagen's strategic approach to bridging the gap between the Taigun and Tiguan models with a stopgap product, a strategy aimed at meeting diverse consumer needs while maintaining brand cohesion and market competitiveness.

A significant portion of our discussion centered on the growing importance of Advanced Driver Assistance Systems (ADAS) features in today's automotive market, particularly from a sales perspective. Mr. Gupta offered compelling perspectives on how Volkswagen integrates ADAS technologies into their vehicles to enhance safety, convenience, and overall driving experience, thus catering to evolving consumer preferences and regulatory standards.

Furthermore, Mr. Gupta provided valuable insights into Volkswagen's newly launched accessories, shedding light on how these offerings complement the brand's vehicle lineup, enhance customization options, and contribute to the overall ownership experience.

Overall, my conversation with Mr. Ashish Gupta offered a comprehensive understanding of Volkswagen's strategic direction, innovative product portfolio, and commitment to delivering exceptional value to customers in an ever-evolving automotive landscape.

liked_videos.title: From Manager To Leader
liked_videos.description:
Share this if you think someone else can benefit from this too.

Hey, you know how we've been chatting about work and where we're headed in our careers?

Well, it's got me thinking that I need to talk to you about how to shift from being a manager to becoming a leader.ü§î

After all, that‚Äôs the path forward for someone to grow to the next levels in their careers and own their true potential.

It's like going from playing a small role in a play to directing the entire production.

When you're managing, it's about keeping things ticking over smoothly, right?

But when you step into leadership, it's a whole new level. It's about having this big-picture vision, inspiring others, and driving real change.

And you know what's cool? It's not just about being the boss or having a fancy title. It's about really understanding yourself, your team, and creating an environment where everyone can shine and grow.üíØ

Leaders aren't just people in charge; they're like coaches, cheerleaders, and visionaries rolled into one. liked_videos.title: 9 Mistakes Every Investor Makes | Why People Lose Money In Stock Market?
liked_videos.description:
Stock Market: Strategies, Pitfalls, and Solutions

Investing in stocks can be thrilling yet challenging. Many investors face hurdles like timing the market, emotional attachments to companies, and neglecting diversification. Let‚Äôs delve into these pitfalls and ways to overcome them.

Timing the Market:
Trying to predict market movements is risky. Instead, focus on long-term investments. Regular contributions and diversification can help mitigate market volatility.

Not Understanding the Business:
Investing without understanding a company‚Äôs fundamentals is akin to gambling. Thorough research is crucial. Analyze the business model, financials, and industry dynamics before investing.

I Love the Company:
Emotional attachment can cloud judgment. Base investment decisions on objective analysis rather than feelings.

Averaging Down:
Buying more shares as the stock price drops can be tempting, but it can lead to further losses. Reevaluate the investment thesis before averaging down.

Tunnel Vision: My Price, My Portfolio:
Focusing solely on target prices or allocations can lead to missed opportunities. Stay flexible and adapt to changing market conditions.

Looking Only at Stock Price:
Stock prices may not reflect a company‚Äôs true value. Conduct fundamental analysis to assess a company‚Äôs health and prospects.

Penny Stock Speculation:
Investing in penny stocks can be risky due to volatility and speculation. Allocate only a small portion of your portfolio to speculative investments and conduct thorough research.

Allocation Problem:
Proper asset allocation is crucial for managing risk. Diversify across different asset classes and sectors to optimize returns.

Waiting to Get Even: The Biggest Blunder:
Holding onto losing investments indefinitely can hinder portfolio growth. Cut losses and reallocate funds to better opportunities.

How to Mitigate:

Why Are You Even Doing This?: 
Align your investment strategy with your goals, time horizon, and risk tolerance.

Automate: Implement automatic investment plans like dollar-cost averaging to maintain discipline.

Play Part: Stay informed but acknowledge that not every market movement can be predicted. Focus on disciplined, diversified, long-term investing.

In conclusion, understanding common pitfalls and implementing mitigation strategies can help investors navigate the stock market more effectively, increasing their chances of achieving long-term financial success.

liked_videos.title: BEST INDEX to invest for 15-20 years? Nifty LargeMidcap 250 Index | Complete Review
liked_videos.description:
The Nifty Large Midcap 250 Index offers several advantages over other indices:

Balanced Exposure: It provides a balanced exposure to both large-cap and mid-cap segments, mitigating the risk associated with either segment's performance. This balanced approach ensures that investors benefit from the stability of large-cap stocks while also tapping into the growth potential of mid-cap stocks.

Diversification: By equally allocating investments between large-cap and mid-cap companies, the index fund offers diversification across various companies, sectors, and market capitalizations. This diversification helps spread risk and potentially enhances returns over the long term.

Optimized Allocation: The index fund invests your money equally between the top 100 large companies and the next 150 midcap companies. This allocation strategy is optimized to capture opportunities across both segments of the market, maximizing the potential for returns while minimizing risk.

Historical Performance: Over various time horizons, the Nifty LargeMidcap 250 Index has demonstrated strong performance relative to other indices such as the Nifty 100 Index and the Nifty Midcap 150 Index. It has outperformed the Nifty 100 Index across multiple long-term periods, indicating its ability to generate superior returns over time.

Return-Risk Ratio: The index exhibits a higher return-risk ratio compared to the Nifty 100 Index over both short and long-term horizons. This suggests that investors can potentially achieve higher returns for a given level of risk by investing in the Nifty LargeMidcap 250 Index compared to the Nifty 100 Index.

Overall, the Nifty LargeMidcap 250 Index offers investors a well-rounded investment opportunity, combining the stability of large-cap stocks with the growth potential of mid-cap stocks, along with the benefits of diversification and historical performance.

Historically over a long term this has outperformed Nifty 50 significantly.

Hey there, fellow go-getter! üëã

Let's have a heart-to-heart about something that might be holding you back in your career journey: overapologizing.

You see, we've been conditioned to say sorry for everything ‚Äì from sharing our ideas to taking up space in a room.

But here's the thing: constantly apologizing diminishes our presence and undermines our confidence.

It's time to rewrite that narrative and step into our power! üí™

Picture this: instead of shrinking ourselves to fit into tiny boxes of societal expectations, we stand tall, speak up, and own our worth.

Because guess what?

You have incredible ideas, unique perspectives, and limitless potential waiting to be unleashed.

So, let's make a pact right here, right now: no more unnecessary apologies.

Instead, let's replace them with assertiveness, self-assurance, and unapologetic confidence.

Imagine the doors that will open, the opportunities that will flow, and the heights you'll reach when you stop apologizing for being you.

You deserve to thrive in your career, to make your mark, and to inspire others with your authenticity and brilliance.

So, let's banish the apologies, embrace our true potential, and watch as our careers soar to new heights.

liked_videos.title: 2X your money in 4 years? | Rule of 72
liked_videos.description:
2X your money every 4 years | Rule of 72
The Rule of 72 is an easy-to-use formula designed to estimate the time needed for an investment to double its value, given a specific rate of return. This rule is particularly useful with compounded interest rates and tends to be most accurate for rates between 6% and 10%. Beyond investments, the Rule of 72 can also be applied to other areas experiencing exponential growth, such as GDP or inflation rates. It's helpful in understanding the long-term impacts of annual fees on the growth of investments. Additionally, the Rule of 72 can assist in calculating the rate of return necessary for an investment to double within a set time frame. In various circumstances, alternative rules like the Rule of 69, Rule of 70, or Rule of 73 might offer more precision.

How Do You Calculate the Rule of 72?
The Rule of 72 is a straightforward way to estimate how long it will take for an investment to double in value. Simply divide 72 by the investment's expected annual return rate to get the number of years it will approximately take for your investment to double.

For example, if you have an investment opportunity that promises an 8% annual compounded rate of return, it will take about nine years (72 / 8 = 9) for the investment to double. This means, if you invest ‚Çπ10,000 at this rate, your investment will grow to ‚Çπ20,000 in 9 years, ‚Çπ40,000 in 18 years, ‚Çπ80,000 in 27 years, and so on.

liked_videos.title: How Nvidia Grew From Gaming To A.I. Giant, Now Powering ChatGPT
liked_videos.description:
Thirty years ago, Taiwan immigrant Jensen Huang founded Nvidia with the dream of revolutionizing PCs and gaming with 3D graphics. In 1999, after laying off the majority of workers and nearly going bankrupt, the company succeeded when it launched what it claims as the world‚Äôs first Graphics Processing Unit (GPU). Then Jensen bet the company on something entirely different: AI. Now, that bet is paying off in a big way as Nvidia‚Äôs A100 chips quickly become the coveted training engines for ChatGPT and other generative AI. But as the chip shortage eases, other chip giants like Intel are struggling. And with all it‚Äôs chips made by TSMC in Taiwan, Nvidia remains vulnerable to mounting U.S.-China trade tensions. We went to Nvidia‚Äôs Silicon Valley, California, headquarters to talk with Huang and get a behind-the scenes-look at the chips powering gaming and the AI boom.

Chapters: 
02:04 ‚Äî Chapter 1: Popularizing the GPU
07:02 ‚Äî Chapter 2: From graphics to AI and ChatGPT
11:52 ‚Äî Chapter 3: Geopolitics and other concerns
14:31 ‚Äî Chapter 4: Amazon, autonomous cars and beyond

PROJECT MADRAS offers a gameplay experience steeped in the rich cultural tapestry of Chennai. Set in the capital city of the TamilNadu where the world's oldest language "TAMIL" thrives, the game brings you a unique cultural journey spanning centuries.

Roam freely through the city's landmarks and neighborhoods, all while pursuing a story that adds purpose to your exploration. PROJECT MADRAS invites you to not just play a game but to be a part of a dynamic culture of Chennai.

liked_videos.description:
When you want to move from manager to leader or executive level, there are certain shifts you need to make in your approach to work. Because what got you to a management position, won't get you into a leadership role. You will need to learn new skills, leadership skills, executive level qualities that will help you advance and get promoted into leadership. 

These skills aren't difficult for you to learn, nor should you be intimidated by them. Simply watch this video and I will guide you through the changes you need to make. And remember, it's not always about doing more, sometimes it's about identifying what you need to do less of (I talk more about this in the video). 

So click on the above video and start learning the how to move from manager to leader or executive role. I encourage you to start implementing these skills early while you're still in a management position. That way, you'll be ready for a leadership promotion when it comes along.

-----

Having a team is absolutely crucial! Your team is who you depend on to carry out all the daily tasks and operations. They work hard to accomplish goals and meet targets. They help you generate revenues and work with you to make your business a successful one. 

What if your team is not motivated? 
If your team is not motivated, the system falls apart. They do not take initiative or be proactive. They do what is asked of them but do not put their heart or soul into it. liked_videos.title: Best Ways to Invest (2025 Edition) | The ULTIMATE INVESTING GUIDE for Beginners
liked_videos.description:
Learn Basic Of Stock Market Investments | https://www.financeboosan.in

‚ÄéFollow the Finance Boosan channel on WhatsApp: https://whatsapp.com/channel/0029Va6xVGJ1iUxff71r8p23

Do this before investing

1. Emergency Fund:
   - Purpose: It serves as a financial safety net in unforeseen circumstances like job loss, medical emergencies, or urgent home repairs.
   - How much to save: Generally, it's recommended to have enough to cover 3-6 months of living expenses.
   - Where to keep it: This fund should be easily accessible, ideally in a high-yield savings account or a liquid fund.

2. Term Insurance:
   - What it is: Term insurance is a type of life insurance that provides coverage at a fixed rate of payments for a limited period. 
   - Importance: It's crucial for those with financial dependents to ensure their family‚Äôs financial security in case of the policyholder's untimely demise.

3. Health Insurance:
   - Why it's needed: Health insurance covers medical expenses, which can be financially devastating without coverage.
   - What to consider: Look for a policy with a sufficient cover, considering factors like family health history, coverage for critical illnesses, and network hospitals.

4. Repay Your Debts:
   - Strategy: Prioritize high-interest debts like credit card balances. Consider debt consolidation or refinancing for better interest rates.
   - Importance: Reducing debt lowers financial risk and interest expenses, freeing up more money for investments.

Next, consider your investment strategy based on risk appetite, investment goals, and time horizon. Here are major categories to consider:

1. Fixed or Recurring Deposits:
   - Characteristics: Safe, predictable returns, best for short-term goals.
   - Consideration: Generally offer lower returns compared to other investment types.

2. Mutual Funds:
   - Types: Equity-Linked Savings Scheme (ELSS) for tax-saving, Index Funds for passive investing - Active Funds for high risk appetite individuals.
   - Benefits: Diversification, professional management, suitable for a range of investment goals.

3. Gold:
   - Options: Sovereign Gold Bonds (SGB), Gold Exchange-Traded Funds (ETFs), and Gold Mutual Funds.
   - Role in Portfolio: Acts as a hedge against inflation and market volatility.

4. Bonds:
   - What they are: Debt instruments where an investor loans money to an entity (corporate or governmental) that borrows the funds for a defined period at a fixed interest rate.
   - Risk and Return: Generally safer than stocks but with lower potential returns.

5. Real Estate:
   - Investment in property: Can be for rental income or capital appreciation.
   - Considerations: Requires significant capital, subject to market risks and liquidity concerns.

6. Direct Stocks:
   - What it entails: Buying shares of individual companies.
   - Considerations: High risk and high potential returns, requires market knowledge and active management.

‚Çπ1 Cr health plan at ‚Çπ390/ month

‚ÄéFollow the Finance Boosan channel on WhatsApp: https://whatsapp.com/channel/0029Va6xVGJ1iUxff71r8p23


3x Monthly Income Rule: Aim to save or invest at least three times your monthly income each year. For instance, if you earn 40K per month, you should have saved or invested 1.2L by year-end. This represents a 25% savings rate, which is slightly below the average savings rate in India (30.2%) but still substantial to start with.

5 Day Rule: Invest or save at least 25% of your income within five days of receiving your paycheck. This can be automated through SIPs (Systematic Investment Plans), RDs (Recurring Deposits), or SSYs (Sukanya Samriddhi Yojanas). For those with irregular income, the key is to invest within five days of receiving the majority of your income.

‚Äú3‚Äù before ‚Äú3‚Äù Rule: Prioritize having an emergency fund, term insurance, and health insurance before investing. An emergency fund should be equivalent to three times your monthly expenses and kept in highly liquid forms like a bank FD or savings account.

40% EMI Debt Repayment Rule: Your EMI (Equated Monthly Installment) or debt payments should not exceed 40% of your total income. If your EMIs are too high, the recommendation is to increase your income to keep the EMI within 40% of your income.

16 EMI Rule: To quickly pay off loans, aim to pay 16 EMIs per year instead of the usual 12. This can significantly reduce the total interest paid and the loan period.

25X Rule: Ensure your term insurance coverage is at least 25 times your annual expenses. This amount of coverage ensures sufficient funds for many years, accounting for inflation and lifestyle maintenance.

Rule of 72: This rule helps estimate the time it takes for an investment to double at a given annual rate of return. For example, at a 12% return rate, it would take about 6 years to double the investment.

liked_videos.title: How to Get Good at Small Talk, and Even Enjoy It
liked_videos.description:
Even if you don‚Äôt think you‚Äôre a natural (or you hate it), anyone can become proficient at this important art using the right tactics and behaviors.

00:00 ‚ÄúSmall talk‚Äù is a misnomer for such an important part of communication.
01:07 Establish appropriate goals.
01:52 Give yourself permission to pause.
03:35 What if you feel like you have nothing smart to say?
04:24 What if I make a mistake or say something dumb?
05:09 What if my problem is that I have too much to say?
06:04 What tools can I use if none of this is natural to me?
07:53 How do I get the conversation started?
09:00 How do I end the conversation (gracefully)?

According to Matt Abrahams, author of "Think Faster, Talk Smarter: How to Speak Successfully When You're Put on the Spot", key strategies include avoiding conventional responses in favor of establishing genuine connections, prioritizing brevity while delivering messages, and speaking authentically without the pressure to be perfect‚Äîwhich means daring to be dull. Fear or nervousness need not deter anyone from communicating effectively on the spot.

Read more: https://hbr.org/2023/09/how-to-shine-when-youre-put-on-the-spot

And there's more by Matt Abrahams on this topic in his new book: https://www.amazon.com/Think-Faster-Talk-Smarter-Successfully/dp/1668010305/

liked_videos.description:
The Stuntman becomes the hero. #TheFallGuyMovie only in theaters May 3.

------

He‚Äôs a stuntman, and like everyone in the stunt community, he gets blown up, shot, crashed, thrown through windows and dropped from the highest of heights, all for our entertainment. And now, fresh off an almost career-ending accident, this working-class hero has to track down a missing movie star, solve a conspiracy and try to win back the love of his life while still doing his day job. What could possibly go right? 

From real life stunt man and director David Leitch, the blockbuster director of Bullet Train, Deadpool 2, Atomic Blonde and Fast & Furious Presents: Hobbs & Shaw and the producer of John Wick, Nobody and Violent Night, comes his most personal film yet. A new hilarious, hard-driving, all-star apex-action thriller and love letter to action movies and the hard-working and under-appreciated crew of people who make them: The Fall Guy. 

Oscar¬Æ nominee Ryan Gosling (Barbie, La La Land, Drive) stars as Colt Seavers, a battle-scarred stuntman who, having left the business a year earlier to focus on both his physical and mental health, is drafted back into service when the star of a mega-budget studio movie‚Äîbeing directed by his ex, Jody Moreno, played by Golden Globe winner Emily Blunt (Oppenheimer, A Quiet Place films, Sicario)‚Äîgoes missing.

While the film‚Äôs ruthless producer (Emmy winner Hannah Waddingham; Ted Lasso), maneuvers to keep the disappearance of star Tom Ryder (Golden Globe winner Aaron Taylor-Johnson; Bullet Train) a secret from the studio and the media, Colt performs the film‚Äôs most outrageous stunts while trying (with limited success) to charm his way back into Jody‚Äôs good graces. But as the mystery around the missing star deepens, Colt will find himself ensnared in a sinister, criminal plot that will push him to the edge of a fall more dangerous than any stunt.

Inspired by the hit 1980s TV series, The Fall Guy also stars Winston Duke (Black Panther franchise) and Academy Award¬Æ nominee Stephanie Hsu (Everything Everywhere All at Once). 

From a screenplay by Hobbs & Shaw screenwriter Drew Pearce, The Fall Guy is produced by Kelly McCormick (Bullet Train, Nobody, Atomic Blonde) and David Leitch for their company 87North, and by Ryan Gosling and by Guymon Casady (Game of Thrones, Steve Jobs and executive producer of the upcoming series Ripley) for Entertainment 360. The film is executive produced by Drew Pearce, Entertainment 360‚Äôs Geoff Shaevitz and the creator of the original Fall Guy television series, Glen A. Larson.

liked_videos.description:
Get a signed copy of Lives Of The Stoics at The Painted Porch Bookshop: https://www.thepaintedporch.com/products/ryan9?variant=40308614299802

For the Stoics, it didn‚Äôt matter what one did for a living, it mattered how they did it. 

Yes, sure, there was the job ‚Äúking,‚Äù but far more important was being a kingly person, the greatest empire was the one that Seneca laid out: command of oneself. 

If we are to aspire to power, this is the one to aspire to. If we want to lead, let us start by leading ourselves. If we want accolades and privileges, let‚Äôs seek to deserve them rather than acquire them.

liked_videos.title: Productivity Guilt   #SHORTS
liked_videos.description:
PRODUCTIVITY GUILT‚Ä¶‚Å£    #SHORTS
That continual nagging feeling that you haven‚Äôt done enough‚Ä¶ That you‚Äôre so far behind‚Ä¶ That you can‚Äôt take a break because you don‚Äôt deserve it‚Ä¶‚Å£
‚Å£
Sound familiar? ü§∑üèª‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è‚Å£
‚Å£
It‚Äôs quite common among high achievers, and could also a ‚Äòsymptom‚Äô of imposter syndrome and high functioning anxiety.‚Å£
‚Å£
If this is something you experience (It is for me!) here are 3 suggestions that might help;‚Å£
‚Å£
1Ô∏è‚É£ Accept You‚Äôll Always Be Imperfect‚Å£
‚Å£
Perfection isn‚Äôt the standard you want to be aiming for‚Ä¶ Instead, strive for ‚Äòhuman‚Äô. What does that mean? Well, you can have high standards and strive for excellence, but also know that you‚Äôre only human and only have so much you can fit in your mind (‚Äòcognitive load‚Äô) 7 into your life. And guess what‚Ä¶ mistakes come with the territory!‚Å£
‚Å£
2Ô∏è‚É£ Don‚Äôt focus on the Gap between Current Self & Ideal Self‚Å£
‚Å£
One of the reasons why you feel this ‚Äòguilt‚Äô is that you‚Äôre not where you want to be. You have this vision of your ‚Äòideal‚Äô self which is more disciplined, more successful, more of who you want to be‚Ä¶ and you become fixated on the giant gap between this state and where you actually are. Instead of looking at the gap, focus on what you‚Äôre doing each day to take one small step closer to the goal state.‚Å£
‚Å£
3Ô∏è‚É£ Prioritize rest‚Å£
‚Å£
One big mistake you might be making if you‚Äôve fallen into the trap of productivity guilt is that you keep pushing to the point of diminishing returns. You‚Äôre no longer ‚Äòproductive‚Äô, but you don‚Äôt stop (‚Äòhello guilt!‚Äô). Yet, if you just took the time to rest, charge your body & replenish your mental battery, get this - you‚Äôd be even MORE productive, getting more done in less time!‚Å£
‚Å£
What about you? Have you experienced productivity guilt?‚Å£
---------------

Argylle
Only In Theaters February 2
https://www.argyllemovie.com/

---
The greater the spy, the bigger the lie.
 
From the twisted mind of Matthew Vaughn (Kingsman franchise, Kick-Ass) comes Argylle, a razor-witted, reality-bending, globe-encircling spy thriller.
 
Bryce Dallas Howard (Jurassic World franchise) is Elly Conway, the reclusive author of a series of best-selling espionage novels, whose idea of bliss is a night at home with her computer and her cat, Alfie. But when the plots of Elly‚Äôs fictional books‚Äîwhich center on secret agent Argylle and his mission to unravel a global spy syndicate‚Äîbegin to mirror the covert actions of a real-life spy organization, quiet evenings at home become a thing of the past.
 
Accompanied by Aiden (Oscar¬Æ winner Sam Rockwell), a cat-allergic spy, Elly (carrying Alfie in her backpack) races across the world to stay one step ahead of the killers as the line between Elly‚Äôs fictional world and her real one begins to blur.
 
The top-flight ensemble cast features Henry Cavill (The Witcher), John Cena (Fast X), Oscar¬Æ winner Ariana DeBose (West Side Story), Grammy winning pop superstar Dua Lipa (Barbie), Emmy winner and Oscar¬Æ nominee Bryan Cranston (Breaking Bad), Emmy winner and comedy icon Catherine O‚ÄôHara (Schitt‚Äôs Creek), Sofia Boutella (Kingsman: The Secret Service), and the legendary Samuel L. Jackson. Alfie is played by Chip, the real-life cat of supermodel Claudia Vaughn (n√©e Schiffer).
 
Argylle is directed and produced by Matthew Vaughn, from a screenplay by Jason Fuchs (Wonder Woman). The film is produced by Matthew Vaughn, Adam Bohling (Kingsman franchise), Jason Fuchs, and David Reid (Kingsman franchise). The executive producers are Adam Fishbach, Zygi Kamasa, Carlos Peres and Claudia Vaughn.
 
Apple Original Films presents, in association with MARV, a Cloudy production. Argylle is distributed by Universal Pictures.

Do you struggle to articulate your thoughts clearly? When you speak, do you get your thoughts muddled and your thoughts come out in a jumbled way? Do you find that your thoughts are clear in your mind, but when you go to speak, they're not clear anymore?! 

Being able to articulate your thoughts clearly doesn't come naturally to many people. In fact, most people are unable to articulate their thoughts well. Sometimes it's because you're trying too hard. Other times it's because you haven't put enough thought into what you want to say before you start to speak.

There are a number of reasons as to why you can't articulate your thoughts clearly. In this video, I share 7 of the most common reasons as to why you struggle to articulate your thoughts clearly.

When we're around the same environment we've been in for so long, people have preconceived ideas of who we are, so if we try anything new like changing our voice to improve our communication skills, it might not always be met with encouragement.

liked_videos.title: Gallagher Explains Pronunciation | Stand-Up | The New Smothers Brothers Comedy Hour
liked_videos.description:
Gallagher performs hilarious stand-up comedy on The New Smothers Brothers Comedy Hour.

The Smothers Brothers, Tom and Dick, are one of the most iconic comedy duos in the history of television. Tom and Dick began performing as a duo in the late 1950s, playing in coffeehouses and clubs in San Francisco. Their act consisted of music, comedy, and witty banter, which quickly gained them a following.

The Smothers Brothers became a household name in the late 1960s with their variety show, The Smothers Brothers Comedy Hour. The show was groundbreaking in its approach to comedy, pushing the boundaries with political satire and social commentary. The show also featured up-and-coming musical acts, including The Doors and The Who, and introduced the world to comedians like Steve Martin and George Carlin.

The Smothers Brothers' irreverent style has made them a beloved and enduring force in American comedy.

liked_videos.title: BLUE BEETLE | OFFICIAL FINAL TRAILER
liked_videos.description:
The Reyes family just got its first superhero.  #BlueBeetle - Only in theaters August 18.

From Warner Bros. Pictures comes the feature film ‚ÄúBlue Beetle,‚Äù marking the DC Super Hero‚Äôs first time on the big screen. The film, directed by Angel Manuel Soto, stars Xolo Maridue√±a in the title role as well as his alter ego, Jaime Reyes.

Recent college grad Jaime Reyes returns home full of aspirations for his future, only to find that home is not quite as he left it. As he searches to find his purpose in the world, fate intervenes when Jaime unexpectedly finds himself in possession of an ancient relic of alien biotechnology: the Scarab. When the Scarab suddenly chooses Jaime to be its symbiotic host, he is bestowed with an incredible suit of armor capable of extraordinary and unpredictable powers, forever changing his destiny as he becomes the Super Hero BLUE BEETLE.

Starring alongside Maridue√±a (‚ÄúCobra Kai‚Äù) are Adriana Barraza (‚ÄúRambo: Last Blood,‚Äù ‚ÄúThor‚Äù), Dam√≠an Alc√°zar (‚ÄúNarcos,‚Äù ‚ÄúNarcos: Mexico‚Äù), Elpidia Carrillo (‚ÄúMayans M.C.,‚Äù the ‚ÄúPredator‚Äù films), Bruna Marquezine (‚ÄúMaldivas,‚Äù ‚ÄúGod Save the King‚Äù), Raoul Max Trujillo (the ‚ÄúSicario‚Äù films, ‚ÄúMayans M.C.‚Äù), with Oscar winner Susan Sarandon (‚ÄúMonarch,‚Äù ‚ÄúDead Man Walking‚Äù), and George Lopez (the ‚ÄúRio and ‚ÄúSmurf‚Äù franchises). The film also stars Belissa Escobedo (‚ÄúAmerican Horror Stories,‚Äù ‚ÄúHocus Pocus 2‚Äù) and Harvey Guill√©n (‚ÄúWhat We Do in the Shadows‚Äù). Soto (‚ÄúCharm City Kings,‚Äù ‚ÄúThe Farm‚Äù) directs from a screenplay by Gareth Dunnet-Alcocer (‚ÄúMiss Bala‚Äù), based on characters from DC. John Rickard and Zev Foreman are producing, with Walter Hamada, Galen Vaisman and Garrett Grant serving as executive producers.

The director‚Äôs creative team behind the scenes includes director of photography Pawel Pogorzelski (‚ÄúMidsommar,‚Äù ‚ÄúHereditary‚Äù), production designer John Billington (‚ÄúBad Boys for Life‚Äù), editor Craig Alpert (‚ÄúDeadpool 2,‚Äù ‚ÄúThe Lost City‚Äù), Oscar-nominated costume designer Mayes C. Rubeo (‚ÄúJojo Rabbit,‚Äù the ‚ÄúThor‚Äù films), visual effects supervisor Kelvin McIlwain (‚ÄúThe Suicide Squad,‚Äù ‚ÄúAquaman‚Äù) and composer Bobby Krlic (‚ÄúMidsommar,‚Äù the ‚ÄúSnowpiercer‚Äù series).

A Warner Bros. Pictures Presentation, a Safran Company Production, ‚ÄúBlue Beetle‚Äù soars into theaters only internationally beginning August 2023 and in North America August 18, 2023. It will be distributed worldwide by Warner Bros. Pictures.

Google's first global fintech center is going to be set up in GIFT City, Gujarat.

CEO Sundar Pichai spoke to PM Modi regarding this recently.

Google will use this center to manage its global fintech products like Google Pay, which is already the second-largest UPI payments app in India.

Google is pretty impressed with what India has done in the digital infrastructure space with things like Aadhar and UPI and it wants to use this to build its future products.

And it chose Gujarat because of GIFT City, a special economic zone near Ahmedabad, which the Indian government is trying to push as a global financial center.

Google setting up its only global fintech center in the country shows India‚Äôs growing prominence in the fintech landscape.

Riots in Paris After Teen Murdered by Police | Vantage with Palki Sharma

Protesters set cars ablaze in Paris after teenager was shot dead by a police officer. The teen was killed after trying to flee a traffic stop. A video of the incident went viral and caused an outpouring of grief and anger in France.

Coorg is one of the most beautiful hill stations in South India. It truly defines the beauty of the Western Ghats. This Coorg Travel Guide covers all the information that you need to know to plan your own Coorg trip. We have travelled to Coorg, covering it comprehensively and making this travel guide showing the best places to visit, budget and luxury hotels, best places to eat, how to reach, bike rentals and other such information.

If you liked our work, you can help us create more such videos by giving us a super thanks right below the video. 
Or you could buy us a few coffees! Head over to https://www.buymeacoffee.com/xploretheearth to contribute!

The end of the road begins. 

Fast X, the tenth film in the Fast & Furious Saga, launches the final chapters of one of cinema‚Äôs most storied and popular global franchises, now in its third decade and still going strong with the same core cast and characters as when it began.

Over many missions and against impossible odds, Dom Toretto (Vin Diesel) and his family have outsmarted, out-nerved and outdriven every foe in their path. Now, they confront the most lethal opponent they‚Äôve ever faced: A terrifying threat emerging from the shadows of the past who‚Äôs fueled by blood revenge, and who is determined to shatter this family and destroy everything‚Äîand everyone‚Äîthat Dom loves, forever.  
 
In 2011‚Äôs Fast Five, Dom and his crew took out nefarious Brazilian drug kingpin Hernan Reyes and decapitated his empire on a bridge in Rio De Janeiro. What they didn‚Äôt know was that Reyes‚Äô son, Dante (Aquaman‚Äôs Jason Momoa), witnessed it all and has spent the last 12 years masterminding a plan to make Dom pay the ultimate price. 
 
Dante‚Äôs plot will scatter Dom‚Äôs family from Los Angeles to the catacombs of Rome, from Brazil to London and from Portugal to Antarctica. New allies will be forged and old enemies will resurface. But everything changes when Dom discovers that his own 8-year-old son (Leo Abelo Perry, Black-ish) is the ultimate target of Dante‚Äôs vengeance. 
 
Directed by Louis Leterrier (Clash of the Titans, The Incredible Hulk), Fast X stars returning cast members Michelle Rodriguez, Tyrese Gibson, Chris ‚ÄúLudacris‚Äù Bridges, Nathalie Emmanuel, Jordana Brewster, Sung Kang, Jason Statham, John Cena and Scott Eastwood, with Oscar¬Æ winner Helen Mirren and Oscar¬Æ winner Charlize Theron. 
 
The film also features an extraordinary new cast including Oscar¬Æ winner Brie Larson as Tess, a rogue representative from the Agency; Alan Richtson (Reacher) as Aimes, the new head of the Agency who doesn‚Äôt hold the same fondness for Dom‚Äôs crew as his predecessor, Mr. Nobody; Daniela Melchior (The Suicide Squad) as a Brazilian street racer with a powerful tie to Dom‚Äôs past; and legendary Oscar¬Æ winner Rita Moreno as Dom and Mia‚Äôs Abuelita Toretto. 
 
Fast X is produced by Neal H. Moritz, Vin Diesel, Justin Lin, Jeff Kirschenbaum and Samantha Vincent. The executive producers are Joseph M. Caracciolo, Jr., David Cain, Chris Morgan, Amanda Lewis and Mark Bomback. www.thefastsaga.com

liked_videos.description:
Learn about watsonx ‚Üí https://ibm.biz/BdvxRe

With all the excitement around chatGPT, it‚Äôs easy to lose sight of the unique risks of generative AI. Large language models (LLMs) -- a form of generative AI -- are really good at creating prose that sounds like a native speaker.  But because they‚Äôre so good at it, large language models may give a false impression they possess actual understanding. They don't! In this video, Phaedra Boinodiris explains the potential risks of relying on large language models to your business, brand, or even society. She also presents mitigation strategies for reducing these risks.

Born and raised in London to Kosovar-Albanian parents Dua Lipa signed to Warner Records in 2015, releasing her self titled debut in 2017 which featured the hit singles, 'Be The One', 'IDGAF', 'Hotter Than Hell' & her first UK #1 hit 'New Rules'. 

Critical success soon followed as Dua Lipa picked up Brit Awards for 'Best Female Solo Artist' and 'Best British Breakthrough Act' as well as Grammy Awards for 'Best New Artist' and 'Best Dance Recording' for the track 'Electricity' in collaboration with Silk City.

Her second internationally acclaimed studio album 'Future Nostalgia' was released in 2020 and included the hit singles 'Don't Start Now, 'Break My Heart', 'Hallucinate' and 'Levitating', with the remix album 'Club Future Nostalgia' following shortly after featuring guest appearances from 'Blackpink', 'Missy Elliott', 'Madonna' and 'Gwen Stefani'.

Our very own Desi Girl, Priyanka Chopra, is back with another incredible story for us! Starring alongside Sam Heughan and featuring new music by Celine Dion, #LoveAgainMovie is coming to cinemas May 12th.

What if a random text message led to the love of your life? In this romantic comedy, dealing with the loss of her fianc√©, Mira Ray sends a series of romantic texts to his old cell phone number‚Ä¶ not realizing the number was reassigned to Rob Burns‚Äô new work phone. A journalist, Rob is captivated by the honesty in the beautifully confessional texts. When he‚Äôs assigned to write a profile of megastar Celine Dion (playing herself in her first film role), he enlists her help in figuring out how to meet Mira in person‚Ä¶and win her heart. Starring Priyanka Chopra Jonas, Sam Heughan and Celine Dion and featuring multiple new songs from Dion, Love Again, written for the screen and directed by Jim Strouse, is only in theaters May 12, 2023.

liked_videos.title: The Flash ‚Äì Official Trailer
liked_videos.description:
On June 16, worlds collide. Watch the official trailer now for The Flash ‚Äì only in theaters. #TheFlashMovie 

Warner Bros. Pictures presents ‚ÄúThe Flash,‚Äù directed by Andy Muschietti (the ‚ÄúIT‚Äù films, ‚ÄúMama‚Äù). Ezra Miller reprises their role as Barry Allen in the DC Super Hero‚Äôs first-ever standalone feature film.

Worlds collide in ‚ÄúThe Flash‚Äù when Barry uses his superpowers to travel back in time in order to change the events of the past. But when his attempt to save his family inadvertently alters the future, Barry becomes trapped in a reality in which General Zod has returned, threatening annihilation, and there are no Super Heroes to turn to. That is, unless Barry can coax a very different Batman out of retirement and rescue an imprisoned Kryptonian‚Ä¶ albeit not the one he‚Äôs looking for. Ultimately, to save the world that he is in and return to the future that he knows, Barry‚Äôs only hope is to race for his life. But will making the ultimate sacrifice be enough to reset the universe? 

‚ÄúThe Flash‚Äù ensemble also includes rising star Sasha Calle, Michael Shannon (‚ÄúBullet Train,‚Äù ‚ÄúBatman v Superman: Dawn of Justice‚Äù), Ron Livingston (‚ÄúLoudermilk,‚Äù ‚ÄúThe Conjuring‚Äù), Maribel Verd√∫ (‚ÄúElite,‚Äù ‚ÄúY tu mam√° tambi√©n‚Äù), Kiersey Clemons (‚ÄúZack Snyder‚Äôs Justice League,‚Äù ‚ÄúSweetheart‚Äù), Antje Traue (‚ÄúKing of Ravens,‚Äù ‚ÄúMan of Steel‚Äù) and Michael Keaton (‚ÄúSpider-Man: Homecoming,‚Äù ‚ÄúBatman‚Äù).

‚ÄúThe Flash‚Äù is produced by Barbara Muschietti (the ‚ÄúIT‚Äù films, ‚ÄúMama‚Äù) and Michael Disco (‚ÄúRampage,‚Äù ‚ÄúSan Andreas‚Äù). The screenplay is by Christina Hodson (‚ÄúBirds of Prey,‚Äù ‚ÄúBumblebee‚Äù), with a screen story by John Francis Daley & Jonathan Goldstein (‚ÄúDungeons & Dragons: Honor Among Thieves,‚Äù ‚ÄúSpider-Man: Homecoming‚Äù) and Joby Harold (‚ÄúTransformers: Rise of the Beasts,‚Äù ‚ÄúArmy of the Dead‚Äù), based on characters from DC. The executive producers 
are Toby Emmerich, Walter Hamada, Galen Vaisman and Marianne Jenkins.

Joining director Muschietti behind the camera are director of photography Henry Braham (‚ÄúGuardians of the Galaxy Vol. 3,‚Äù ‚ÄúThe Suicide Squad‚Äù), production designer Paul Denham Austerberry (‚ÄúIT Chapter Two,‚Äù ‚ÄúThe Shape of Water‚Äù), editors Jason Ballantine (the ‚ÄúIT‚Äù films, ‚ÄúThe Great Gatsby‚Äù) and Paul Machliss (‚ÄúThe Gentlemen,‚Äù ‚ÄúBaby Driver‚Äù), and costume designer Alexandra Byrne (‚ÄúDoctor Strange,‚Äù ‚ÄúGuardians of the Galaxy‚Äù); the score is by Benjamin Wallfisch 
(‚ÄúThe Invisible Man,‚Äù the ‚ÄúIT‚Äù films).

Warner Bros. Pictures presents a Double Dream/a Disco Factory production of an Andy Muschietti film, ‚ÄúThe Flash.‚Äù It will be distributed worldwide by Warner Bros. Pictures and is set to open in theaters in North America on June 16, 2023 and internationally beginning 14 June 2023.

music_videos.description:
#amazonmusic  #saiabhyankkar  #artistdiarieswithamazonmusic

Artist Diaries by Amazon Music India features musicians talking about their story with personal and musical milestone anecdotes which helped shape them up into the artists they are today. We catch them in their essence , sometimes in a never-seen-before place like their home, their first gig venue or catch them walking on the beach or a recording studio, to candidly share with the world the person behind the persona.

Talented music composer and young prodigy Sai Abhyankkar gives us an insight into his music process and life after both his viral chartbusters Kachi Sera and Asa Kooda. Fun, light hearted and yet quite a wise approach to life already, watch Sai open up about his favorite things to do and what he plans to do next in this episode of Artist Diaries

About Dua Lipa:
Born and raised in London to Kosovar-Albanian parents Dua Lipa signed to Warner Records in 2015, releasing her self titled debut in 2017 which featured the hit singles, 'Be The One', 'IDGAF', 'Hotter Than Hell' & her first UK #1 hit 'New Rules'. 

Critical success soon followed as Dua Lipa picked up Brit Awards for 'Best Female Solo Artist' and 'Best British Breakthrough Act' as well as Grammy Awards for 'Best New Artist' and 'Best Dance Recording' for the track 'Electricity' in collaboration with Silk City.

Her second internationally acclaimed studio album 'Future Nostalgia' was released in 2020 and included the hit singles 'Don't Start Now, 'Break My Heart', 'Hallucinate' and 'Levitating', with the remix album 'Club Future Nostalgia' following shortly after featuring guest appearances from 'Blackpink', 'Missy Elliott', 'Madonna' and 'Gwen Stefani'. 

#DuaLipa #LoveAgain

Synopsis:
When they ran to save their lives for the first time, they were mere 12-year-old boys, and the world called them 'refugees'.

The war of 1971 gave birth to a new country - Bangladesh. It also gave birth to two young orphans - Bikram and Bala. They witnessed the war and its aftermath, where the world tried to trample over them. Fighting for survival, they clung to each other and escaped to Calcutta.

Before they knew the world, they knew each other. Such was their bond, such was their friendship.

Each time they sought new beginnings, each time they would rise, the world would crush them down. So, they fought again... and again. Together they were unbeatable. They were unstoppable. They were inseparable.

In the years that passed, Bikram and Bala, became Calcutta's most loved, most celebrated, most reckless, most fearless and most powerful GUNDAY!

They had everything... then, one fine day, bells rang...

Nandita, the most beautiful cabaret dancer, walked into their lives, and they lost everything to her. Their murky world turned magical and colourful. They fell head over heels in love with her.

But that was only a blissful lull before an impending storm...

And then entered ACP Satyajeet Sarkar, the right for every wrong, a law for every outlaw and a counter force for Bikram and Bala.

What follows from here is the most sensational-most thrilling-most dramatic story ever told!

music_videos.title: 14 Years Still Running? Vinnaithaandi Varuvaayaa| AR Rahman, Gautham Menon | Rahman Music Sheets 144
music_videos.description:
Can you imagine a film running for 14 days with Housefull board outside the theatre? But a film running for 14+ years is beyond imagination. Right? Wrong. Vinnaithaandi Varuvaayaa also known as VTV is in theatres for more than 14 years. Many call it Dilwale Dulhania Le Jayenge or DDLJ of South India. Starring Shahrukh Khan & Kajol ‚Äì DDLJ is running in theatres since 1995. VTV is proving to be DDLJ of ARR. Besides the story and performances, Music by AR Rahman helped it connect with the audiences. We celebrate VTV by going back in time for behind the scene stories of the film & its music. Director Gautham Vasudev Menon Opens Up.  Rahman Music Sheets 144

RAHMAN MUSIC SHEETS ‚Äì A series to track three decades of an incredible musical journey of Oscars and Grammys winner A.R. Rahman.

music_videos.title: Vinnaithaandi Varuvaayaa - Hits, Misses & A Sequel| AR Rahman, Gautham Menon| Rahman Music Sheets145
music_videos.description:
‚ÄúMagic shouldn‚Äôt be recreated. ‚Äú Why not? The Mystery Unfolds. AR Rahman composed music for 3 films. Two were super-hits & one flopped. Why?  Vinnaithaandi Varuvaayaa (VTV) - A Tamil Blockbuster, released in 2010 is still running in theatres. Its Telughu version Ye Maaya Chesave proved to be a super-hit film. But its Hindi remake Ekk Deewana Tha flopped. Why? Director Gautham Vasudev Menon explains. And why he made a sequel to VTV that too during Covid Lockdown ‚Äì featuring the original cast of Simbu & Trisha. And of course getting onboard AR Rahman with his music. Rahman Music Sheets 145

RAHMAN MUSIC SHEETS ‚Äì A series to track three decades of an incredible musical journey of Oscars and Grammys winner A.R. Rahman.

music_videos.title: Generative AI in a Nutshell - how to survive and thrive in the age of AI
music_videos.description:
Basically a full day AI course crammed into 18 mins of drawing & talking. Target audience: Everyone.
NEWS: Book is now available: https://leanpub.com/ainutshell
NEWS: Course is now available: https://www.ymnig.ai/courses/prompt-engineering-in-a-nutshell-online

Covers questions like What is generative AI, how does it work, how do I use it, what are some of the risks & limitations. Also covers things like autonomous agents, the role of us humans, prompt engineering tips, AI-powered product development, origin of ChatGPT, different types of models, and some tips about mindset around this whole thing. 

Here is the full drawing:
https://blog.crisp.se/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/generative-AI-in-a-nutshell.png

Voice translations:
- Playlist with a bunch of AI voice translations: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ojLUcaqbLBM&list=PL-u8jDo3b1vnzUtiOfLliB2tbDLwVXiqb
- French: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=AkPW3zWHA7w
- German: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Dgu5utapmk0
- Hindi: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gZdUcxqKCe4
- Kurdish (Sorani): https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bvscuBrd3b0
- Ukrainian: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rUqIzty9hkM
- Urdu: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VFy6mvcOXoc

Would you like to make a voice translation? ElevenLabs can do really voice translation which even sounds like me :)
You can also do a manual dub with your own voice if you prefer. Whatever works best.
1. Check out https://elevenlabs.io/docs/dubbing/studio
2. Make the video & upload it to youtube or somewhere.
3. Make sure the description shows that this is an AI translation, and include a link to the original video.
4. Send a link to me (for example via a comment) and I'll add it above.

You can decide if you want to host it on your youtube channel or if I should host it. 

If you have practical questions you can ask Stefan Kirschnick, he made the German dub and is happy to provide support. https://www.linkedin.com/in/stefankirschnick/

Follow Dua Lipa:
Instagram:  https://dualipa.co/instagram
Facebook: http://dualipa.co/facebook
TikTok: https://www.tiktok.com/@dualipaofficial
Twitter: http://dualipa.co/twitter
YouTube: https://dualipa.co/youtube

About Dua Lipa:
Born and raised in London to Kosovar-Albanian parents Dua Lipa signed to Warner Records in 2015, releasing her self titled debut in 2017 which featured the hit singles, 'Be The One', 'IDGAF', 'Hotter Than Hell' & her first UK #1 hit 'New Rules'. 

Critical success soon followed as Dua Lipa picked up Brit Awards for 'Best Female Solo Artist' and 'Best British Breakthrough Act' as well as Grammy Awards for 'Best New Artist' and 'Best Dance Recording' for the track 'Electricity' in collaboration with Silk City.

Her second internationally acclaimed studio album 'Future Nostalgia' was released in 2020 and included the hit singles 'Don't Start Now, 'Break My Heart', 'Hallucinate' and 'Levitating', with the remix album 'Club Future Nostalgia' following shortly after featuring guest appearances from 'Blackpink', 'Missy Elliott', 'Madonna' and 'Gwen Stefani'. 

#DuaLipa #GoodInBed #FutureNostalgia

music_videos.title: Veera Raja Veera | thebalaboys  | PS2 #ponniyinselvan #ps2
How Filmmakers Rejected but Ad. World Embraced @ARRahman | Rajiv Menon |Rahman Music Sheets 77
music_videos.description:
Can you recall advertisement films composed by Rahman ! His music was called ‚ÄòCrap‚Äô and rejected by filmmakers. But the world of advertising was more adventurous. Rahman changed the sound on Indian advertisements and jingles, much before he redefined the sound of film music forever with Roja. Filmmaker, Cinematographer Rajiv Menon opens up about advertisement commercials and jingles Rahman created. 
Rahman Music Sheets ‚Äì Episode 77

Rahman Music Sheets ‚Äì A series to track three decades of an incredible musical journey of Oscars and Grammys winner A.R. Rahman

About Dua Lipa:
Born and raised in London to Kosovar-Albanian parents Dua Lipa signed to Warner Records in 2015, releasing her self titled debut in 2017 which featured the hit singles, 'Be The One', 'IDGAF', 'Hotter Than Hell' & her first UK #1 hit 'New Rules'. 

Critical success soon followed as Dua Lipa picked up Brit Awards for 'Best Female Solo Artist' and 'Best British Breakthrough Act' as well as Grammy Awards for 'Best New Artist' and 'Best Dance Recording' for the track 'Electricity' in collaboration with Silk City.

Her second internationally acclaimed studio album 'Future Nostalgia' was released in 2020 and included the hit singles 'Don't Start Now, 'Break My Heart', 'Hallucinate' and 'Levitating', with the remix album 'Club Future Nostalgia' following shortly after featuring guest appearances from 'Blackpink', 'Missy Elliott', 'Madonna' and 'Gwen Stefani'.

other_videos.title: Deep Dive into LLMs like ChatGPT
other_videos.description:
This is a general audience deep dive into the Large Language Model (LLM) AI technology that powers ChatGPT and related products. It is covers the full training stack of how the models are developed, along with mental models of how to think about their "psychology", and how to get the best use them in practical applications. I have one "Intro to LLMs" video already from ~year ago, but that is just a re-recording of a random talk, so I wanted to loop around and do a lot more comprehensive version.

Instructor
Andrej was a founding member at OpenAI (2015) and then Sr. Director of AI at Tesla (2017-2022), and is now a founder at Eureka Labs, which is building an AI-native school. His goal in this video is to raise knowledge and understanding of the state of the art in AI, and empower people to effectively use the latest and greatest in their work.
Find more at https://karpathy.ai/ and https://x.com/karpathy

other_videos.title: Karpathy Vibe Coding Full Tutorial with Cursor (Zero Coding)
other_videos.description:
Today we talked about the concept and execution of vibe coding, a method where you speak your coding ideas into existence using cutting‚Äêedge AI tools. We explored how to use Cursor Composer alongside Sonnet and WhisperFlow to generate, edit, and run code with minimal manual intervention. The tutorial guided viewers through setting up a project from a Next.js template, cloning a repository, and managing API keys through an .env file to maintain secure credentials. Additionally, the video detailed the process of building a ChatGPT clone using the latest OpenAI API, complete with real-time debugging and iterative improvements on design elements such as input fields, sidebars, and smooth text animations. The discussion also emphasized the importance of keeping the AI prompt context minimal for optimal performance, and it provided insights on how to save and upload projects to GitHub effortlessly. Finally, we touched on integrating real-time voice interaction using the 11Labs API to further enhance the coding experience and pay homage to AI pioneers like Karpathy

Footnotes

Perplexity Spaces (Just like Custom GPT's) Prompt:
i am making app in nextjs:
user is going to give input that they want to put in their site:
you're job is to find a method to do that:
describe what the api does, then output example code. then put a direct link to find the api key.

other_videos.title: Guangzhou autonomous driving bus experience: My first time in a self-driving car
other_videos.description:
Hello everyone! Today, I'm taking you on a tour to experience Guangzhou's driverless bus. Guangzhou has a total of four autonomous bus routes, and the one I'm taking you on today is a route that doesn't require any tickets or reservations. This self-driving bus has many advantages, such as being smooth, having a good view, and being very comfortable to ride. It's a great experience for those who get carsick.

I'll also take you on a tour of a route that runs through the city center. This route has a steering wheel and a safety driver, and it requires advance reservations, so it's a bit more complicated.

Finally, we'll visit a building on Guangzhou's Yuejiang West Road, which is a new business center that Guangzhou is focusing on developing. Many large companies will have offices here. This area also has an autonomous bus route.

other_videos.title: How China‚Äôs New AI Model DeepSeek Is Threatening U.S. Dominance
other_videos.description:
A little-known AI lab out of China has ignited panic throughout Silicon Valley after releasing AI models that can outperform America‚Äôs best despite being built more cheaply and with less-powerful chips. DeepSeek, as the lab is called, unveiled a free, open-source large-language model in late December that it says took only two months and less than $6 million to build.  The new developments have raised alarms on whether America‚Äôs global lead in artificial intelligence is shrinking and called into question big tech‚Äôs massive spend on building AI models and data centers. In a set of third-party benchmark tests, DeepSeek‚Äôs model outperformed Meta‚Äôs Llama 3.1, OpenAI‚Äôs GPT-4o and Anthropic‚Äôs Claude Sonnet 3.5 in accuracy ranging from complex problem-solving to math and coding. CNBC‚Äôs Deirdre Bosa has the story. This video also includes Bosa‚Äôs full interview with Perplexity CEO Aravind Srinivas.

other_videos.title: *YUMMIEST* COOKER BROWNIE RECIPE #shorts
other_videos.description:
Episode 3 of #NoOvenNoProblem ‚òÄÔ∏è, a series where I make your favourite desserts at home WITHOUT an oven üíÅüèª‚Äç‚ôÇÔ∏èMonsoon season calls for warm, chocolaty and fudgy Brownies and this version in a cooker has to be one of the easiest ways to enjoy these delights without much hassle üôåüèª‚ù§Ô∏è

Ingredients 
ü§åüèª1/2 cup butter (100g)
ü§åüèª1/4 cup dark chocolate (43g)
ü§åüèª6 tbsp jaggery
ü§åüèª3/4 cup milk, warm
ü§åüèª1/2 cup wholewheat flour
ü§åüèª6 tbsp cocoa powder
ü§åüèª1/3 cup milk chocolate chunks (58g)
ü§åüèªChocolate chips, for top

Method
1. Spread a layer of salt at the bottom of a cooker and set it in low to medium  heat. Place a hollow stand in the middle and cover the cooker with the lid, remove the whistle and let it preheat for 10 mins. 
2. Grease a 6 inch square pan with butter or oil and line it with parchment paper leaving handles on two ends for easy lifting after baking.
3. Add butter and chocolate in a bowl and melt it in a microwave at 30 seconds intervals till completely melted.
4. Add jaggery powder and milk to the above mixture and mix well. 
5. Dump in the flour and cocoa powder into this mixture and form a smooth lump-free batter. 
6. Fold in the milk chocolate chunks evenly into the batter and transfer the batter into the greased pan. Sprinkle some more chocolate chips on top of the batter.
7. Carefully place the brownie pan inside the cooker and bake for 25-30 mins. 
8. Let the brownies come at room temperature before demoulding and slicing. You can also refrigerate the brownies for 30 mins for sharper edges.

other_videos.description:
Harvard Professor of happiness, Arthur Brooks, turns the tables on the idea of the "bucket list" as a way of achieving satisfaction, showing us where real joy and contentment are far more likely to be found. Arthur C. Brooks is the William Henry Bloomberg Professor of the Practice of Public Leadership at the Harvard Kennedy School and Professor of Management Practice at the Harvard Business School.

Before joining the Harvard faculty in 2019, he served for 10 years as president of the Washington, D.C.-based American Enterprise Institute (AEI), one of the world‚Äôs leading think tanks. Under his leadership, the Institute more than doubled its annual revenues, deepened its outreach to leaders across the ideological spectrum and expanded its research portfolio to include work on poverty, happiness and human potential.

Brooks is the author of 12 books, including the #1 New York Times bestseller ‚ÄúFrom Strength to Strength.‚Äù He is also a columnist for The Atlantic and host of the podcast ‚ÄúHow to Build a Happy Life with Arthur Brooks.‚Äù Brooks gives more than 100 speeches per year around the U.S., Europe and Asia. This talk was given at a TEDx event using the TED conference format but independently organized by a local community. Learn more at https://www.ted.com/tedx

other_videos.title: Why Planes Follow This Invisible Path Across the Atlantic ‚úàÔ∏è Jet Stream Highway üåç
other_videos.description:
Ever wondered why planes flying over the Atlantic üåä seem to follow a narrow, invisible path? ‚úàÔ∏è It‚Äôs all thanks to the incredible Jet Stream Highway! üí®‚ú® This powerful, fast-moving air current helps guide planes across the ocean, making flights not only shorter ‚è±Ô∏è but also more efficient üí∏ and safer üõ°Ô∏è. Picture a constant stream of planes moving in perfect sync along this ‚Äòinvisible highway‚Äô - but how do they avoid collisions, especially with no radar coverage üì° in the middle of the Atlantic? üö¶‚úàÔ∏è Find out why flights from the USA üá∫üá∏ to Europe üá™üá∫ are typically faster thanks to this high-speed wind üå¨Ô∏è But there‚Äôs more - an intricate system called the North Atlantic Tracks üó∫Ô∏è functions like an air traffic map. Every day, experts analyze shifting jet streams and weather patterns to create these safe ‚Äòtracks‚Äô for planes to follow. Pilots request permission to join these paths based on altitude, speed, and distance, keeping every flight safe and efficient. From fuel savings ‚õΩ to increased speeds üí® these invisible highways are an impressive feat of coordination that keeps our skies organized and our trips smooth.

other_videos.title: Why are CARS SO EXPENSIVE in India? | A Case Study | tbh
other_videos.description:
In recent years, the cost of cars in India has been steadily rising, creating significant challenges for the middle class. What was once considered a luxury item has now become a near-essential mode of transportation, yet the affordability gap continues to widen. The increasing car prices can be attributed to several complex factors that impact the overall cost structure.

Taxation plays a crucial role in determining car prices in India. The government levies multiple taxes, including Goods and Services Tax (GST), road tax, registration charges, and additional state-specific levies. These taxes can add substantial amounts to the base price of a vehicle. For instance, the GST rates vary between 5% and 28% depending on the type and value of the car, significantly inflating the final price.
Manufacturing costs have also risen due to several factors. 

The implementation of stricter safety and emission norms requires manufacturers to invest in advanced technologies and more sophisticated manufacturing processes. Additionally, raw material costs, including steel, aluminum, and electronic components, have increased globally. The transition towards electric and hybrid vehicles has further pushed up development and production expenses.

Import duties on crucial components and the need for localization add another layer of complexity to pricing. While the government encourages domestic manufacturing through initiatives like Make in India, the automotive supply chain still faces challenges that contribute to higher costs.

The result is a challenging landscape for middle-class consumers, who find themselves stretching their budgets to own a vehicle that has become increasingly necessary for daily life in India's rapidly developing urban and suburban environments.

other_videos.title: Can you save tax by transferring to Spouse's account? Housewife's tax implications
other_videos.description:
Join Learner's Community : https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCmfl6VteCu880D8Txl4vEag/join
Official Website - Courses & Learning Materials : https://www.financeboosan.in  

Clubbing of Income Under Indian Tax Laws
Clubbing of Income refers to the inclusion of another person's income in the taxpayer's total income for tax computation purposes. This concept is aimed at preventing tax evasion by taxpayers who might otherwise transfer their income or assets to others, typically family members, to reduce their tax liability.

The provisions governing clubbing of income are outlined in Sections 60 to 64 of the Income Tax Act, 1961. Here‚Äôs an overview:

1. Transfer of Income without Transfer of Assets (Section 60)
If a person transfers income from an asset to another person without transferring the ownership of the asset, the income from such an asset is taxed in the hands of the transferor.
Example: If Mr. A owns a property and transfers the rental income to his spouse without transferring the property itself, the rental income will still be taxed in Mr. A's hands.

2. Revocable Transfer of Assets (Section 61)
If a person transfers an asset under a revocable arrangement, the income from such an asset will be taxed in the hands of the transferor.
A revocable transfer is one where the transferor retains the right to reclaim the asset or income.
Example: Mr. A transfers a property to his son but retains the right to revoke the transfer. In such a case, the income from the property is taxed in Mr. A's hands.

3. Income of Spouse (Section 64(1)(ii))
If an individual‚Äôs spouse earns income from an entity where the individual has substantial interest, and the spouse does not possess technical or professional qualifications, the income is clubbed with the income of the individual.
Substantial interest typically means holding at least 20% of the equity shares or profits in the entity.
Example: Mrs. A works in a company where Mr. A has a 30% shareholding. If Mrs. A has no technical or professional qualification for the job, her salary will be clubbed with Mr. A‚Äôs income.

4. Income from Assets Transferred to Spouse (Section 64(1)(iv))
Income from assets transferred directly or indirectly to the spouse without adequate consideration is clubbed with the income of the transferor, except where the asset is transferred under an agreement to live apart.
Example: If Mr. A gifts a house to Mrs. A, the rental income from the house will be taxed in Mr. A‚Äôs hands.

5. Income from Assets Transferred to Son‚Äôs Wife (Section 64(1)(vi))
If an individual transfers assets to their son's wife without adequate consideration, the income from such assets is clubbed with the income of the transferor.
Example: Mr. A gifts shares to his daughter-in-law. The dividend income from these shares will be taxed in Mr. A‚Äôs hands.

6. Income of Minor Child (Section 64(1A))
The income of a minor child is clubbed with the income of the parent whose total income (excluding the child‚Äôs income) is greater.
There are certain exceptions where the child‚Äôs income is not clubbed, such as income earned by a minor from manual work, or from an activity involving the minor‚Äôs talent, or income of a minor child suffering from a disability as specified under Section 80U.
The parent can claim an exemption of up to ‚Çπ1,500 per child per year on the income that is clubbed.

7. Implications of Clubbing of Income
Clubbing can lead to a higher tax liability since the income is added to the transferor‚Äôs total income.
The clubbed income is taxed at the transferor's applicable slab rate, which might be higher than that of the recipient.

8. Prevention of Misuse
The provisions are designed to prevent misuse, such as transferring assets or income to relatives in lower tax brackets to reduce the overall tax burden.
The tax authorities are vigilant in ensuring that these rules are not circumvented through artificial transactions.

Conclusion
The concept of clubbing of income plays a significant role in ensuring that tax liabilities are not reduced unfairly through the transfer of assets or income. It is important for taxpayers to understand these provisions to comply with tax laws and avoid penalties or additional taxes. Proper tax planning and consultation with a tax professional can help manage these aspects effectively.

other_videos.title: Multi-cap funds: A smarter way to invest in mid and small caps?
other_videos.description:
Mid-cap and small-cap funds are among the most sought-after mutual funds. However, their high volatility is a problem. In this video, we find out if multi-cap funds can be a better way to invest in mid and small caps. 

Multi-cap funds are required to invest at least 25% of their assets each in large, mid and small caps. So, at any point, they have 50% assets invested in mid and small caps. Their large-cap exposure helps provide the required stability. So, multi-cap funds can be both rewarding and less volatile.

Few other diversified categories provide this return mix. For example, flexi-cap funds tend to be large-cap heavy and large & mid-cap funds tend to be underweight in small caps. So, multi-cap funds are in a distinguished position.

But the analysis of multi-cap funds is not easy as they came into being only in 2021. They have an interesting history that you can learn more about in the video. So, to analyse these funds, we had to create a multi-cap fund. We did so by taking the Nifty 100, Nifty Midcap 150 and Nifty Smallcap 250 total-return indices and then allocating assets to them as per the asset allocation of multi-cap funds over the last 2 years. We also rebalanced the resulting proxy multi-cap fund on a yearly basis.

We then compared the performance of this proxy multi-cap fund with the mid-cap and small-cap indices. The comparison revealed that not only did the proxy multi-cap fund do considerably well on the returns front but it also offered less volatility and better downside protection. 

Though the study had its limitations, it can be concluded that multi-cap funds can be a good way to invest in mid and small caps. Plus, they can also take care of asset allocation across market caps.

other_videos.title: Surviving Market Meltdowns: Key Lessons from the Sensex Falls | Dhirendra Kumar Shares Expert Advice
other_videos.description:
In this episode of Investors' Hangout, Dhirendra Kumar, an expert in mutual funds and market strategies, explains how to navigate market meltdowns and turn them into opportunities.¬†
From understanding market cycles to aligning your investment goals and practising asset allocation, Dhirendra provides invaluable advice on surviving and thriving during periods of market volatility. He discusses the importance of long-term investing, why some sectors are hit harder during downturns, and how asset allocation can balance risk and reward. Learn how to stay calm and make informed decisions to emerge stronger after a market fall.

Chapters:
00:04 Introduction
00:28 What key strategies can investors use to stay calm and avoid panic selling during a market meltdown?
02:57 What do historical Sensex recoveries teach us about timing the market, and why is staying invested critical for long-term success?
04:35 How can investors balance risk and opportunity during a downturn, and what role should asset allocation play in surviving market volatility?
06:13 Viewer's Question - If all funds are doing well (3 to 5-star-rated), how does having too many funds translate into a higher expense ratio and lower returns?
09:13 Closing
09:23 Key Takeaways:
- Align with Long-Term Goals: Invest in equities for the long run, not for short-term needs.
- Avoid Daily Monitoring: Don't obsess over daily market movements; focus on the long term.
- Understand Market Cycles: Markets recover over time, so stay patient during downturns.
- Use Asset Allocation: Balance risk by diversifying between equities and fixed income.
- Choose the Right Fund: Start with a balanced or hybrid fund for stability, not speculative ones.

other_videos.description:
Welcome to the 300th episode of Investors' Hangout! In this special masterclass, Dhirendra Kumar, CEO of Value Research, delivers a powerful session on building wealth with mutual funds. If you're a young investor or someone new to the world of finance, this episode is packed with timeless insights and practical advice on creating long-term wealth through smart, disciplined investing.

Dhirendra Kumar covers:
- Why simplicity beats complexity in investing
- The critical role of starting early and forming good financial habits
- How to beat inflation and grow your wealth with equity investments
- The importance of asset allocation and tax planning
- Common investing mistakes to avoid and the value of patience

This masterclass also includes a lively Q&A session with young professionals where Dhirendra answers real-life questions on everything from balancing debt and investments to choosing funds for different financial goals. Whether you're a beginner or looking to refine your strategy, this episode offers clear guidance to help you navigate the world of mutual funds and build a secure financial future.

other_videos.title: How China Uses Mexico To Avoid U.S. Tariffs
other_videos.description:
For the first time in more than two decades Mexico overtook China as the largest importer of goods to the U.S.

Mexican goods imported to the U.S. totaled $475 billion in 2023 about $20 billion higher than the previous year. Feuling that trend are simmering trade tensions between Beijing and Washington, an effort to bring U.S. imports closer to home and a burgeoning Mexican manufacturing base. But there‚Äôs another factor at play. To avoid American tariffs Chinese companies are using Mexico as a backdoor to the U.S. So how is China able to circumvent U.S. tariffs and what are logistic companies doing to prepare for the upcoming boom in Mexican trade. CNBC traveled to Mexico City and El Paso to find out.

other_videos.title: Swiggy‚Äôs IPO makes 500 employees crorepatis, 9 executives to gain over Rs 50 cr
other_videos.description:
Food delivery giant Swiggy‚Äôs initial public offering (IPO) is set to make 500 of its employees crorepatis through employee stock options (ESOPs). The Bengaluru-based food and commodities aggregator listed at 7.7% premium of Rs 420 on the National Stock Exchange today. The company has a total of 231 million outstanding ESOPs, valued at over Rs 9,000 crore, the company said in its DRHP report. A total of 5,000 employees are set to benefit from the ESOP payout. Swiggy‚Äôs ESOP payout is set to top that of Walmart-backed e-commerce company Flipkart, which had a $1.5 billion payout.
Swiggy's founders and top management were allocated ESOPs worth Rs 2,600 crore in its latest stock ownership plan

other_videos.title: 'We must accept the results of this election':  Kamala Harris concedes election
other_videos.description:
Former U.S. President and Republican Donald Trump made a comeback as he won a second term in office, defeating Vice-President Kamala Harris, the Democratic nominee, to become the 47th President of the United States. 

‚Äú‚Ä¶We‚Äôre going to help our country heal,‚Äù Mr. Trump said, speaking in West Palm Breach, Florida, before he had reached the 270 mark. Mr. Trump spoke of the coming of a ‚Äúgolden age‚Äù for America, saying, ‚ÄúAmerica has given us an unprecedented and powerful mandate. We have taken back control of the Senate.‚Äù

In her concession speech on Wednesday at Howard University, her alma mater, Kamala Harris said, ‚ÄúWe must accept the results of this election.‚Äù She encouraged supporters to continue fighting for their vision of the country after her loss to Donald Trump. The Democratic vice president said the battle would continue ‚Äúin the voting booth, in the courts and in the public square.‚Äù

‚ÄúWhile I concede this election, I do not concede the fight that fueled this campaign,‚Äù Harris said.

other_videos.title: Top 5 Index Funds in India to Buy & Hold Forever
other_videos.description:
Subscribe for more: https://www.youtube.com/@remoterish?sub_confirmation=1

In this video, I challenge the popular concept of forever buying and holding mutual funds. 

While many investors follow this advice, I believe it's unrealistic. 

Every year, you see a new list of top mutual funds across large-cap, mid-cap, flexi-cap, and more. If the list keeps changing, how can anyone expect to buy and hold a fund forever?

I explain why mutual funds constantly evolve, with fund managers changing, strategies shifting, and market cycles turning. 

Over time, these factors can dramatically affect your returns. In contrast, index funds provide a much more stable option for long-term investing. 

With index funds, the role of the fund manager is minimal, and the portfolio simply tracks the top companies in the market, making them more reliable for holding over the long term. 

There's no need to worry about constant shifts in performance or new funds entering the spotlight every year.

I explore why index funds are easier to hold forever, how they minimize the emotional and strategic noise that comes from market speculation, and why this approach works better for long-term wealth building. 

I also touch on why it's crucial to avoid being swayed by flashy marketing from mutual funds, which often promise high returns but require constant attention and changes to your strategy.

If you're someone who's aiming to build a long-term portfolio with minimal intervention and wants to stay focused on the core principles of compounding, this video will give you a practical guide on how to achieve that through index investing.

Key Takeaways:
The myth of holding mutual funds forever.
How index funds offer simplicity and stability.
Why market noise from fund managers can disrupt long-term plans.
The power of sticking with funds that change the least.
