other_videos.title: How China is designing flood-resistant cities
other_videos.description:
These "sponge city" designs resist floods and increase biodiversity to help us adapt to a changing climate.

This episode is presented by Delta. Delta doesn‚Äôt have a say in our editorial decisions, but they make videos like this possible. For more information, visit http://www.delta.com/sustainability.

Subscribe to our channel and turn on notifications (üîî) so you don't miss any videos: http://goo.gl/0bsAjO

From rising sea levels in Mumbai to unbearable heat in Houston, cities around the world are feeling the effects of climate change. Unfortunately, they don‚Äôt always have the right infrastructure to handle its impacts ‚Äî which is one reason why cities are beginning to reimagine urban design. One of these designs is a ‚Äúsponge city.‚Äù

Although one city design certainly won‚Äôt save us from the effects of climate change, ‚Äúsponge cities‚Äù can help with how we live with it. 

Here are some studies and articles we used to inform our reporting:

Biodiversity ‚Äî our strongest natural defense against climate change: https://www.un.org/en/climatechange/science/climate-issues/biodiversity

Sponge City, Shenzhen Explores the Benefits of Designing with Nature: https://www.lincolninst.edu/publications/articles/sponge-city-shenzhen-explores-benefits-designing-with-nature

Sponge City Practices in China: From Pilot Exploration to Systemic Demonstration: https://www.mdpi.com/2073-4441/14/10/1531

The ocean is rising ‚Äî and so is Miami‚Äôs skyline: https://www.vox.com/climate/23872640/coastal-climate-ocean-rising-miami-florida-building

Sponge Cities: Integrating Green and Gray Infrastructure to Build Climate Change Resilience in the People‚Äôs Republic of China: https://www.adb.org/sites/default/files/publication/838386/adb-brief-222-sponge-cities-prc.pdf

How Is Climate Change Affecting Floods?: https://www.nytimes.com/article/flooding-climate-change.html

other_videos.title: Stop Buying On Every Dip | The Right SIP Plus Lump Sum Strategy
other_videos.description:
A lot of smart investors use the SIP-plus-lump sum strategy for better returns. They maintain an ongoing SIP in mutual funds, and when markets fall, they invest a lump sum amount to benefit from market corrections. Recently, on 4th June, we saw markets fall close to 6% following unexpected election results. On that day, many investors seized the opportunity to invest lump sums, aiming to capitalize on the correction.

But does this strategy work? In this video, we dive deep into the data to find surprising answers. We'll explore three key aspects: the type of correction (whether to invest when markets fall or when valuations are low), the size of the correction (ideal investment points at 5%, 10%, or 15% drops), and the optimal investment horizon to maximize returns with this strategy. Watch the video to discover which combination of variables produces the highest returns and how you can optimize your investment strategy.

other_videos.description:
In this podcast episode of Young Turks Reloaded, we delve into Zerodha‚Äôs remarkable journey, from its serendipitous beginnings to becoming a ‚Çπ8,000 crore fintech giant, all while remaining bootstrapped and avoiding external capital. The discussion explores how Zerodha‚Äôs founders prioritized ideology and direction over conventional paths to success, focusing on efficiency, innovation, and sustainability. The pandemic marked a pivotal growth moment, helping shape their evolving fintech vision, transitioning from serving traders to building a broader, community-oriented platform.

The podcast also covers Zerodha‚Äôs unique stance on IPOs, where the firm emphasizes freedom and innovation over raising capital through public listing. Regulatory challenges, particularly in India‚Äôs private market investments, have driven their philosophy of long-term thinking and compliance, ensuring resilience in the face of changing regulations.

Additionally, Zerodha‚Äôs thoughtful approach to AI and technology is explored, showing how they balance efficiency gains with employee well-being, while addressing misconceptions around AI‚Äôs impact on jobs. Zerodha‚Äôs future focus is on creating a community-driven financial ecosystem, leveraging strategic partnerships, and embracing continuous innovation. Throughout, philosophical debates and constant inquiry fuel their growth and long-term strategy.

other_videos.title: How Amazon Failed to Understand India? - Business Case Study
other_videos.description:
00:00 - Intro
02:00 - Arrival in India
03:21 - Strategy in India
06:16 - How is it Failing?
12:05 - Future of Amazon

Amazon's journey in India has been marked by both promise and challenges. In 2015, Jeff Bezos declared India as Amazon‚Äôs most crucial market after the US. India, with its rapid economic growth and emerging e-commerce landscape, appeared to be a perfect opportunity for Amazon to extend its global dominance. Initially, Amazon invested heavily, pouring over $5 billion into its operations, and significantly shaping the country‚Äôs e-commerce sector alongside Flipkart. Amazon's infrastructure, customer experience, and seller services helped the company gain a strong foothold, especially in tier-1 cities, positioning it as a major player in India's e-commerce landscape.

However, in recent years, Amazon's growth in India has slowed, and it is facing significant competition from newer players like Meesho, Zepto, and Blinkit. In FY-23, Amazon India‚Äôs revenue grew by only 3.4%, the slowest growth in its history. One of the primary reasons for this slowdown is the shift in India‚Äôs e-commerce landscape. India is not a homogenous market but is divided into different segments based on income and consumption patterns, often referred to as India 1, India 2, and India 3. Amazon initially targeted the premium segment, India 1, which accounted for a small portion of the population but the majority of the country's consumption. However, by 2017, this segment started reaching saturation, and the growth in e-commerce began shifting towards tier-2 and tier-3 cities (India 2 and 3), which have different needs and behaviors.

The arrival of Reliance Jio and the subsequent rise of internet penetration brought millions of new consumers from smaller towns online. These consumers, however, were more price-sensitive and less familiar with online shopping, and Amazon failed to adapt quickly to their needs. Meesho capitalized on this gap by introducing innovative solutions, such as selling through WhatsApp groups and enabling local resellers, which built trust and made online shopping accessible for this new wave of customers. Meesho‚Äôs zero-commission model and faster payment cycles for sellers also gave it a competitive advantage, especially among smaller sellers.

Another challenge for Amazon is the rise of quick commerce in India. Post-pandemic, companies like Blinkit revolutionized the market by offering 10-minute grocery and product deliveries. This sector, which didn‚Äôt exist a few years ago, is growing at an explosive rate, with Blinkit already being valued at $13 billion‚Äîhalf of Amazon India's valuation. While Amazon has always prided itself on fast delivery, it has yet to make significant moves into the quick commerce space, leaving it vulnerable to competitors.

Furthermore, government regulations have added to Amazon's difficulties. India‚Äôs regulatory environment is increasingly cautious of foreign dominance in crucial sectors like e-commerce. In 2019, new rules prevented companies like Amazon from selling products from brands in which they held a stake, forcing Amazon to remove hundreds of thousands of products from its platform. The Indian government‚Äôs push for a more open and competitive e-commerce sector, through initiatives like ONDC, also threatens Amazon's future in the country.

In response to these challenges, Amazon is now shifting focus to other sectors, such as cloud computing and digital payments. However, Amazon‚Äôs core e-commerce business remains essential to its overall strategy, as it serves as the distribution network for its other ventures. If the company cannot regain its momentum in e-commerce, its ability to expand into new areas may also be hampered. Despite the setbacks, the future of Amazon in India remains uncertain, and it will need to rethink its approach to compete in this rapidly changing market.

other_videos.title: AI tools for software engineers, but without the hype ‚Äì with Simon Willison (Co-Creator of Django)
other_videos.description:
On the first episode of the Pragmatic Engineer Podcast, I am joined by Simon Willison. Simon is one of the best-known software engineers experimenting with LLMs to boost his own productivity: he‚Äôs been doing this for more than three years, blogging about it in the open.

Simon is the creator of Datasette, an open-source tool for exploring and publishing data. He works full-time developing open-source tools for data journalism, centered on Datasette and SQLite. Previously, he was an engineering director at Eventbrite, joining through the acquisition of Lanyrd, a Y Combinator startup he co-founded in 2010. Simon is also a co-creator of the Django Web Framework. He has been blogging about web development since the early 2000s.

In today‚Äôs conversation, we dive deep into the realm of Gen AI and talk about the following: 

‚Ä¢ Simon‚Äôs initial experiments with LLMs and coding tools
‚Ä¢ Why fine-tuning is generally a waste of time‚Äîand when it‚Äôs not
‚Ä¢ RAG: an overview
‚Ä¢ Interacting with GPTs voice mode
‚Ä¢ Simon‚Äôs day-to-day LLM stack
‚Ä¢ Common misconceptions about LLMs and ethical gray areas 
‚Ä¢ How Simon‚Äôs productivity has increased and his generally optimistic view on these tools
‚Ä¢ Tips, tricks, and hacks for interacting with GenAI tools
‚Ä¢ And more! 

‚Äî

other_videos.title: Off Script with The Hollywood Reporter India | Filmmakers Roundtable
other_videos.description:
In a never-before seen interaction, join THR India editor Anupama Chopra as she sits down with five visionary directors from across India for an insightful roundtable discussion on the first episode of Off Script with THR, India. This star-studded panel features the incomparable Vetri Maaran and Pa. Ranjith from Tamil cinema, game-changers Karan Johar and Zoya Akhtar from Hindi cinema, and the multifaceted Mahesh Narayanan from Malayalam cinema.

In this engaging conversation, the directors delve into the current state of Indian cinema, discussing everything from the challenges of the theatrical business to the evolving landscape of streaming platforms. They share personal insights into their creative processes, favorite aspects of filmmaking, and the unique challenges they face in their respective industries.

The discussion touches on crucial topics such as the Hema committee report, representation of caste violence in cinema, the willingness of big stars to take on challenging roles and the importance of maintaining artistic integrity while navigating commercial pressures. This roundtable offers a rare glimpse into the minds of some of India's most influential filmmakers, showcasing their passion, creativity, and dedication to their craft.

other_videos.title: This is how your JOB will make you rich.
other_videos.description:
We often see people on the internet labelling the 9-5 job as "modern slavery." But is that really the case?

It's widely believed that the modern 9-5 job comes with numerous problems ‚Äî long working hours, low wages, job insecurity, and office politics. Given all these issues, many think, "If I'm so skilled, why not just start something on my own?" And of course, the biggest question remains: Can a 9-5 job truly make you rich?

But is all of this actually true? Are our expectations from a 9-5 job valid, or are they shaped by the unrealistic narratives the internet often sells us?

other_videos.title: How Namma Yatri Ended Ola and Uber's Dominance?
other_videos.description:
The video discusses the challenges faced by drivers working for cab-hailing services like Ola and Uber in India, particularly regarding commissions and delayed payments. It talks about a new business model introduced by Namma Yatri, a part of the government-led ONDC, aimed at addressing these issues. This model eliminates commissions and instead charges drivers a fixed subscription fee, offering them more control over their earnings and immediate payment from customers. Since its launch, this model has gained significant traction, with over 3 lakh drivers joining Namma Yatri, leading to its expansion into other cities.

The success of Namma Yatri's zero-commission model has put pressure on traditional players like Ola and Uber to adopt similar strategies. Rapido, another cab-hailing service, was the first to adopt this model, prompting Ola and Uber to follow suit to avoid losing drivers to competitors. This shift signifies a significant disruption in the cab-hailing industry, challenging the dominance of Ola and Uber and potentially reshaping the market dynamics.

Furthermore, Namma Yatri has announced plans to enter the cab-hailing business in Bengaluru, further intensifying competition in the sector. This move poses a significant threat to Ola and Uber, which have established themselves over the years. Ola, in particular, is gearing up for an IPO, adding more pressure on the company to adapt to changing market trends.

Sanjeev Bikhchandani is the founder of InfoEdge and has been one of the boldest investors in the Indian Startup Ecosystem. 

Sanjeev first invested in Zomato back in 2010 and has since put in around 17.5 Million dollars. That money is now worth 3.7 Billion dollars, a staggering 217x return on investment. 

Sanjeev‚Äôs other successful bet was in PolicyBazaar, a company he has backed since 2007. His investment in the company of 69 Million dollars, is now worth 1.02 Billion dollars. 

But the question is, how did he achieve this?

In one word, the answer is ‚Äòpatience‚Äô. See, a typical VC firm has a fund cycle of 10 years, which means they have to exit before that. 

But the Indian market takes longer periods to give big returns, almost 15 years in these two cases.

other_videos.title: Tutorials 2-Building Multi AI Agents Chatbots With External Tools With LangGraph
other_videos.description:
LangGraph is a library for building stateful, multi-actor applications with LLMs, used to create agent and multi-agent workflows. Compared to other LLM frameworks, it offers these core benefits: cycles, controllability, and persistence. LangGraph allows you to define flows that involve cycles, essential for most agentic architectures, differentiating it from DAG-based solutions. As a very low-level framework, it provides fine-grained control over both the flow and state of your application, crucial for creating reliable agents. Additionally, LangGraph includes built-in persistence, enabling advanced human-in-the-loop and memory features.

Regina Barzilay from MIT created a major breakthrough in detecting early stage breast cancer. She also led the team that used machine learning to discover Halicin, the first new antibiotic in 30 years. 

David Silver is Principal Research Scientist at Google DeepMind. He led the AlphaGo team that built the AI to defeat the world‚Äôs best human player of Go. 

Paolo Pirjanian founded Embodied, and is a pioneer in developing emotionally intelligent robots to aid child development.

other_videos.title: AI's trillion dollar time bomb
other_videos.description:
There‚Äôs a time bomb ticking in the AI space: spending is too high, and returns are too low. Megacaps like Meta, Google and Amazon have seen capex spending surge as they throw cash at building out the infrastructure to stay ahead of the AI game. Microsoft in particular has spent billions at a premium valuation, and shelled out $13 billion investing in OpenAI while Apple was reportedly able to secure a partnership with the startup darling for free just 18 months later. That could be a warning for the broader AI space, as experts sound the alarm on the widening gap between what companies are spending on AI, and what they‚Äôre getting back from it.

other_videos.title: Vector Database: A Must-Know Guide
other_videos.description:
This must-know guide will provide you with all the information you need to understand vector databases and how they are used in generative AI like LLM.

Unlike traditional databases, vector databases excel in identifying similarities between data objects, making them indispensable for tasks like movie recommendations and AI-driven insights.

What You'll Learn:

1. Understanding Traditional Databases: Learn how SQL databases organize data in rows and columns, and their limitations with fuzzy queries.
2. Introduction to Vector Databases: Discover how data is represented as multi-dimensional vectors, capturing the essence of text, images, and more.
3. Indexing and Querying: See how vector databases convert data into vectors for efficient storage and retrieval, using algorithms like word embeddings.
4. Real-World Applications: Explore a practical example of recommending movies using vector similarities.
5. Advanced Concepts: Delve into vector storage, indexing algorithms, distance metrics, and query processing engines.
6. Future of AI with RAG: Understand how vector databases enhance Retrieval Augmented Generation (RAG) for contextually relevant AI responses.

other_videos.title: Why the US has so many tornadoes
other_videos.description:
Tornado Alley experiences more tornadoes than anywhere else in the world ‚Äî why?
This video is presented by CuriosityStream: https://www.curiositystream.com/Vox

Become a Video Lab member! http://bit.ly/video-lab

The United States experiences more tornadoes than any other country, averaging over 1,200 per year. Most of those twisters are touching down in the central part of the country in an area called ‚ÄúTornado Alley.‚Äù While the boundaries of this tornado hotbed are disputed, there‚Äôs no denying that something is going on here ‚Äî and it all has to do with geography. 

The map we use in this video for Tornado Alley boundaries is from NOAA ‚Äî you can find that and more information on their website: https://www.ncdc.noaa.gov/climate-information/extreme-events/us-tornado-climatology/tornado-alley

Information on tornado averages and trends can also be found at NOAA:
https://www.ncdc.noaa.gov/climate-information/extreme-events/us-tornado-climatology/trends

You may have noticed on our graphic around the one-minute mark that many of the Southeastern US states are prone to tornadoes as well. This is because they‚Äôre part of an area called ‚ÄúDixie Alley.‚Äù The main difference between this area and Tornado Alley that tornadoes in Dixie Alley are more likely to touch down in the fall, while Tornado Alley experiences twisters in the early spring. This happens for the reasons outlined in the video above. This article offers a fairly compelling comparison of the two: 
http://citeseerx.ist.psu.edu/viewdoc/download?doi=10.1.1.660.5241&rep=rep1&type=pdf

Finally, this video offered a simplified explanation of a really complex weather phenomenon. This National Geographic article does a really great job breaking it down again and also offers information on why it‚Äôs so hard to track and predict tornadoes:
https://news.nationalgeographic.com/2015/05/150511-tornadoes-storms-midwest-weather-science/

other_videos.description:
Let's Ride. 
#TwistersMovie is only in theaters July 19.
_____ 
 
This summer, the epic studio disaster movie returns with an adrenaline-pumping, big-screen thrill ride that puts you in direct contact with one of nature‚Äôs most wondrous‚Äîand destructive‚Äîforces. 
 
From the producers of the Jurassic, Bourne and Indiana Jones series comes Twisters, 
a current-day chapter of the 1996 blockbuster, Twister. Directed by Lee Isaac Chung, the Oscar¬Æ nominated writer-director of Minari, Twisters stars Daisy Edgar-Jones (Where the Crawdads Sing), Glen Powell (Top Gun: Maverick) and Anthony Ramos (Transformers: Rise of the Beasts) as equal forces, with opposing motivations, who come together to try to predict, and possibly tame, the immense power of tornadoes.

Edgar-Jones stars as Kate Carter, a former storm chaser haunted by a devastating encounter with a tornado during her college years who now studies storm patterns on screens safely in New York City. She is lured back to the open plains by her friend, Javi (Ramos) to test a groundbreaking new tracking system. There, she crosses paths with Tyler Owens (Powell), the charming and reckless social-media superstar who thrives on posting his storm-chasing adventures with his raucous crew, the more dangerous the better.
 
As storm season intensifies, terrifying phenomena never seen before are unleashed, and Kate, Tyler, Javi and their crews find themselves squarely in the paths of multiple storm systems converging over central Oklahoma in the fight of their lives.

Twisters features an exciting new cast, including Nope‚Äôs Brandon Perea, Golden Globe winner Maura Tierney (Beautiful Boy), Sasha Lane (American Honey), Harry Hadden-Paton (The Crown), David Corenswet (We Own This City), Daryl McCormack (Peaky Blinders), Tunde Adebimpe (Leave the World Behind), Katy O‚ÄôBrian (Ant-Man and the Wasp: Quantumania), Nik Dodani (Atypical), Kiernan Shipka (Chilling Adventures of Sabrina) and Paul Scheer (Black Monday).

From Amblin, Twisters is directed by Lee Isaac Chung and is produced by Oscar¬Æ nominee Frank Marshall (Jurassic and Indiana Jones franchises) and by Patrick Crowley (Jurassic and Bourne franchises). The screenplay is by Mark L. Smith, writer of the Best Picture nominee The Revenant, from a story by Joseph Kosinski (Oblivion), based on characters created by Michael Crichton & Anne Marie Crichton. The executive producers are Academy Award¬Æ winner Steven Spielberg, Thomas Hayslip and Ashley Jay Sandberg. Twisters will be distributed by Universal Pictures domestically and by Warner Bros. Pictures internationally.

other_videos.title: Watch this before selling your mutual funds | Money Psychology
other_videos.description:
If you're an investor who does a lot of research before picking stocks or mutual funds for your portfolio, you've probably counted on the magic of compounding over the long term. But, can you accurately predict when to exit your mutual funds? The answer is yes!

There are tons of videos out there about how to buy the best mutual funds for your portfolio, but very few talk about when to sell them. The truth is, you can only truly benefit from compounding if you know the right time to sell your mutual funds.

In this video, we'll cover the good and bad reasons people sell their mutual funds and talk about SWP (Systematic Withdrawal Plan) and its usefulness in goal based investing. Also, check out the resources below. 

Do show us your love in the comments below!

Dior's $2800 Bag Costs Just $57 to Make! | Vantage with Palki Sharma

Recent investigations have revealed that two of Italy's most prominent luxury fashion houses, Dior and Giorgio Armani, pay a surprisingly low amount to produce handbags that retail for thousands of dollars. Documents examined by the authorities show that Dior paid a supplier only $57 to make bags that sell for about $2,780. So, what explains this stupendous price markup? Are you paying for quality handbags or are you paying for the brand? Palki Sharma answers the questions.

other_videos.title: Ep #18 | WTF, Alcohol is a $70B Business in India? | Nikhil Kamath explores Gaps & Opportunities
other_videos.description:
India has had a long, colourful, and mixed history with Liquor over the centuries, with ancient fermented drinks and traditional liquors like feni and toddy. India today, holds the third-largest market for alcoholic beverages globally, which is remarkable given the challenging business environment of red tape-ism, varying excise duties across states and much more.
In episode #18 of ‚ÄúWTF is‚Äù Podcast, we have Founders of different sectors in the Liquor Industry of India. Abhishek Khaitan, MD of Radico Khaitan, One of the oldest and largest manufacturers of Indian Made Foreign Liquor (IMFL) in India; Minakshi Singh, Co-founder of SideCar, India‚Äôs only entry in the top 100 of the World‚Äôs Best Bars; Shuchir Suri, Co founder of Gin Explorer‚Äôs Club, India‚Äôs biggest gin festival with a footfall of over 100,000 people per edition; and Suraj Shenai, Founder of Goa Brewing Co, crafting ‚Äònon-conformist, modern‚Äô beers that challenge the traditional dominance of German and Belgian flavours.

If Euphemism for patriotism is outrightly sold to people, across the world in different pockets, can the same brand-building tactics work for Indian Products too?

other_videos.title: How Distributed Lock works | ft Redis | System Design
other_videos.description:
Distributed locking is a key concept in ensuring data integrity and consistency in distributed systems. In this video we explore distributed locking mechanisms including centralized locking, token-based locking, and quorum-based locking, explaining their principles, advantages, and limitations.

We then look into Redis based Redlock, a widely adopted quorum-based locking algorithm that provides high availability and fault tolerance. We break down the Redlock algorithm step by step, highlighting how it leverages multiple Redis instances to achieve consensus on lock acquisition.

Throughout the video, I emphasize the importance of distributed locking in maintaining data integrity and preventing conflicts in concurrent systems. 

We also discuss real-world applications of distributed locking, such as managing inventory in e-commerce systems and coordinating access to shared resources in cloud environments.

other_videos.title: Population of the USA üá∫üá∏ Why 80% of Americans Live East of This Line?
other_videos.description:
Have you ever wondered why a significant majority of Americans reside east of a particular line, while only a smaller fraction occupies the western part of the United States? üá∫üá∏ Uncover the geographic factors that contribute to this fascinating phenomenon. Discover how the majority of western residents are concentrated in California, Oregon, and Washington within this line, accounting for a significant portion of the region's population. Furthermore, explore the astonishing statistic that only 9% of Americans live in half of the mainland US, equivalent to the population of New York City alone. üò± Learn about the primary reason behind this geographical distribution: the imposing Rocky Mountains, which serve as a natural barrier to Pacific Ocean rains, creating a phenomenon known as the "rain shadow." Delve into how these mountains hinder cloud movement, impacting precipitation patterns across the country. Explore the intricate interplay between precipitation patterns and wind currents, particularly the influence of Gulf of Mexico winds along the 100th meridian. Understand how these factors contribute to the creation of dry, agriculturally unsuitable regions and their subsequent impact on population density.
The journey through America's diverse geography and uncover the complex dynamics that shape where Americans choose to call home.

Vijay plays Sivakasi, a welder who left his obscure village to seek his fortunes in Chennai, and has never returned. He falls in love with Asin, who wants his parents to come to her house and ask for her hand in marriage. Vijay goes to his native village, only to find his father , his mother living in disgrace in her own house, and his sister married and packed off in a disgraceful manner - all through the machinations of elder brother played by Prakashraj. The rest of the movie is about how Vijay sets right everything.

other_videos.description:
What is a GPU and how is it different than a GPU? GPUs and CPUs are both silicone based microprocessors but they differ in what they specialize in. GPUs specialize in parallel computations, and CPUs specialize in serial computations. 
While GPUs are known for a key component of getting the great graphics you want in your gamming, they are also known in the Machine Learning and AI Community for helping crunch millions of parameters needed to train a machine.

other_videos.title: The Rise of India as a Global Economic Power | Bloomberg Originals Marathon
other_videos.description:
A collection of India-centric documentaries covering its fast-growing economy, China relations, religious tensions, the rise of Narendra Modi and industry deep dives. 

0:00 - How India Can Win China's Growth Crown
7:29 - How Narendra Modi Took Power in India
30:34 - What This $200 Million Temple Says About Modi‚Äôs India
40:08 - Inside Luxury‚Äôs Secret India Supply Chain
48:08 - How India's Drug Exports May Have a Safety Problem
57:12 - Inside Modi's Dangerous Bet on Alternative Medicine
1:04:12 - India‚Äôs Obesity Time Bomb 

How India Can Win China's Growth Crown: https://youtu.be/Q6q8TI2oUmc Originally published April 5, 2024

China‚Äôs economy is slowing and India is vying to take its place as the world‚Äôs biggest driver of growth. But the path is filled with obstacles. What does India need to fix before it can take China‚Äôs crown? 

Read the full story: https://trib.al/Ubb7SZX

How Narendra Modi Took Power in India: https://youtu.be/FLQoCNzoT2o Originally published May 15, 2024

Narendra Modi, India‚Äôs 73-year-old prime minister, is both highly popular and deeply polarizing. How did he work his way to the top of Indian politics, and what do his policies mean for the country‚Äôs future, both at home and on the world stage?

Bloomberg Originals speaks with childhood friends, government officials and former associates who have seen Modi up close over the years, seeking to understand how his core beliefs may have shaped his decision-making. We also show how he has sought to simultaneously make himself a champion of the poor and a friend to billionaires.

Sitting at the top of the world‚Äôs most populous nation and one of its fastest growing economies, Modi occupies a uniquely important and powerful position in geopolitics, global trade and finance ‚Äì especially as China‚Äôs growth has slowed. We explain how he got there, and what may come next.

Read more about How Narendra Modi Is Preparing for a Thousand-Year Legacy on Bloomberg: https://www.bloomberg.com/features/2024-modi-legacy-india-elections/

What This $200 Million Temple Says About Modi‚Äôs India: https://youtu.be/Dfxtx1Y0T9E Originally published January 19, 2024

When Indian Prime Minister Narendra Modi inaugurates the new Hindu temple in Ayodhya, many will see it as the capstone of his 10 years in power. Built on the site of a former mosque at a cost estimated at more than $200 million, the temple shows how his Bharatiya Janata Party has become a seemingly unstoppable electoral machine. And the timing of the inauguration, just months before national elections, may boost the election prospects of Modi and his fellow Hindu nationalists. 

Inside Luxury‚Äôs Secret India Supply Chain: https://youtu.be/Qy2JWUOwTWQ Originally published September 28, 2023

Some of your ‚ÄúMade in France‚Äù luxury items are actually made in India. For decades, fashion houses obscured their business ties to developing nations where labor is cheap, and hard-to-find handicraft skills plentiful.

Today, credit sharing remains contested, even as laws tighten around transparency. We set out to investigate what‚Äôs behind a garment label.

How India's Drug Exports May Have a Safety Problem: https://youtu.be/3BoQsnqC5zM Originally published December 15, 2023

Hospitals around the world use drugs from a small but crucial Indian supplier. In Colombia four kids died and more than a hundred fell ill. In a months-long investigation, Bloomberg Businessweek found that, despite a track record of safety lapses and quality concerns, the manufacturer continued selling its drugs. 

Read the full story: http://www.trib.al/NPh1C4F

Inside Modi's Dangerous Bet on Alternative Medicine: https://youtu.be/msJOeyHQOoQ Originally published February 28, 2024

India‚Äôs alternative medicine industry is booming as ancient principles of healthy living gain new traction, thanks in part to support from Narendra Modi‚Äôs government.  ‚ÄúAyurveda‚Äù, an ancient medical system that has existed in India for centuries, is flourishing with help from holistic-living influencers with vast reach on Instagram and YouTube. But there's a dark side to Ayurveda‚Äôs popularity.

Some doctors in India are seeing patients suffer serious injuries from long term use of ayurvedic medicines. Medical professionals trying to raise awareness about the dangers of alternative medicines have faced lawsuits and even government intervention.

India‚Äôs Obesity Time Bomb: https://youtu.be/VLZXmSToMi8 Originally published November 3, 2023

Almost 1 in 4 adults is considered overweight or obese in India. As junk food giants push into developing nations with weaker public health awareness, campaigners are calling for tougher regulation.

As of last week, salaries of 3.5 lakh government employees are delayed, the one who got their salary are not able to withdraw the entire amount, social security schemes of 55 lakh people have been put on hold and now the state of kerala is asking the center to bail it out! And if you are wondering why politics and economics are important for you as a citizen, I need to tell you that, in our case study of 2022, we presented a case study from the RBI‚Äôs research which clearly alerted everyone about this problem!! And like I said in 2022, even today if you don't pay attention to your state‚Äôs finances, your state will be in the same condition as kerala!!

So if you want to be a sharp student of economics or a sensible citizen, you need to understand, 
How did Kerela fall into an economic crisis?
In Spite of being so educated and development focused, why couldn't the leaders of kerala save the state from this crisis? 
And most importantly, as citizens of India, what are the lessons we needs to learn from the fall of Kerala?

other_videos.title: All You Need to Know about BUY NOW PAY LATER | Ep. #17 ft. Axio
other_videos.description:
Axio, formerly known as Capital Float, is India's leading BNPL, NBFC, and credit platform, designed to meet the financial needs of both salaried and self-employed individuals across the country. Founded by Sashank Rishyasringa and Gaurav Hinduja in 2013, Axio offers core products including Buy Now Pay Later, personal loans, and an app for tracking finances. Leveraging advanced technology, they serve around 9 million customers, process 7 million loans a month, and generate a revenue of 8000 crores annually.

Backed by marquee investors like Elevation Capital (formerly SAIF Partners), Sequoia India, Lightrock, Creation Investments Capital Management LLC, Ribbit Capital, and Amazon, Axio is committed to revolutionizing financial accessibility in India.

The Off Campus team visited their office in Bangalore and met with the founders and their team to gain insights into the business behind running a digital credit company.

For more content like this, subscribe to our channel @mastersunion.

other_videos.title: How Compounding Works? Problem with Stocks & Mutual Funds
other_videos.description:
Compounding is a phenomenon that works wonders over time. It's like a snowball rolling down a hill, gathering more snow and growing larger as it goes. At its core, compounding involves earning returns on both the original investment and the returns that have already been generated. This creates a snowball effect where wealth accumulates exponentially over time.

Here's how it works: let's say you invest Rs. 1000 in a stock or mutual fund that earns an annual return of 10%. In the first year, you earn Rs. 100 in returns, bringing your total investment to Rs. 1100. In the second year, you earn 10% on the entire Rs. 1100, not just the original Rs. 1000. This means you earn Rs. 110 in returns, bringing your total investment to Rs. 1210.

As the years go by, this process repeats itself, with your investment growing larger and larger with each passing year. The longer you leave your money invested, the more powerful compounding becomes. Over time, even small, regular investments can grow into significant sums.

Compounding is often referred to as the "eighth wonder of the world" because of its remarkable ability to grow wealth over time. However, it's important to remember that compounding works best over long periods. It requires patience and discipline to let your investments grow and resist the temptation to withdraw your money prematurely.

By harnessing the power of compounding and staying invested for the long term, you can build wealth steadily and achieve your financial goals. So start early, invest regularly, and let the power of compounding work its magic for you.

Compounding isn't just about finances; it's a principle applicable to life's many facets. Small, consistent efforts, like daily exercise, can compound into significant improvements in health. Similarly, acts of kindness in relationships build trust over time. Skill-building, with just 15 minutes of practice daily, leads to expertise. This universal principle underscores the power of consistency in achieving incremental gains. So, whether in finances or personal growth, embrace the compounding effect, and watch as steady efforts yield remarkable results across all areas of life.

other_videos.title: DynamoDB Partition Key: 5 Things You Must Know Before It's Too Late (AWS)
other_videos.description:
Choosing the right partition key is crucial to achieving good performance and scalability in DynamoDB. 

Hi Guys, this is Abi from Gokce DB and in this video, you are going to learn 5 things that you should know before choosing a partition key.

1. A good partition key should have high cardinality, meaning that it should have a large number of distinct values. This ensures that the data is evenly distributed across the partitions, which results in better performance and scalability. Examples include emailid, employee_no, customerid, sessionid & orderid.

2. Choose a partition key that will be frequently queried. The partition key is used to retrieve data from DynamoDB, so it should be chosen based on the most common queries that will be performed. If a partition key is rarely queried, it will result in uneven distribution of data and may lead to hot partitions, which can cause performance issues.

3. Avoid using always increasing values as partition keys such as a timestamps. This can cause all new data to be written to the same partition, resulting in a hot partition. As mentioned earlier, uneven distribution of data can impact the performance of the database.

4. Consider using composite partition keys which means you should try to combine more than one attribute to form a unique key. For example, you could use a combination of customer ID, product ID and country code as a composite partition key if that meets your access pattern.

5. Cache popular items when there is a high volume of read traffic using Amazon DynamoDB Accelerator or DAX.  It is a fully managed, in-memory cache for DynamoDB that will prevent reads of unusually popular items from swamping partitions.

Remember, you cannot change partition key after the table is created. 
By following these best practices, you can choose a partition key that will optimize performance and scalability in Amazon DynamoDB.

other_videos.title: Capacity Planning and Estimation: How much data does YouTube store daily?
other_videos.description:
Back-of-the-envelope calculations are often expected in system design questions. They help logically state the parameters influencing a result, and estimating the capacity requires multiple estimations on the way. Also lets us individually state our assumptions.

Eg: Estimate the hardware requirements to set up a system like YouTube.
Eg: Estimate the number of petrol pumps in the city of Mumbai.

Chapters
00:06 Storage Requirements
01:20 Supplementary storage requirements
03:54 Back of Envelope calculations
05:38 Youtube caching estimation
08:58 Youtube video processing estimation
12:14 Conclusion

------STORAGE
Let's start with storage requirements:
About 1 billion active users.
I assume 1/1000 produces a video a day.
Which means 1 million new videos a day.

What's the size of each video?
Assume the average length of a video to be 10 minutes. 
 Assume a 10 minute video to be of size 1 GB. Or...
A video is a bunch of images. 10 minutes is 600 seconds. Each second has 24 frames. So a video has 25*600 = 150,000 frames.
 Each frame is of size 1 MB. Which means (1.5 * 10^5) * (10^6) bytes = 150 GB.
This estimate is very inaccurate, and hence we must either revise our estimate or hope the interviewer corrects us. Normal video of 10 minutes is about 700 MB.

As each video is of about 1GB, we assume the storage requirement per day is 1GB * 1 million = 1 PB. 

This is the bare minimum storage requirement to store the original videos. If we want to have redundancy for fault tolerance and performance, we have to store copies. I'll choose 3 copies. 
That's 3 petabytes of raw data storage.
What about video formats and encoding? Let's assume a single type of encoding, mp4, and the formats will take a 720p video and store it in 480, 360, 240 and 144p respectively. That means approximately half the video size per codec.

If X is the original storage requirement = 1 PB,
We have X + X/2 + X/4 + X/8 == 2*X.
With redundancy, that's 2X * 3 = 6*X.

That's 6 PB(processed) + 3PB (raw)  == 10 PB of data. About 100 hard drives. The cost of this system is about 1 million per day.

For a 3 year plan, we can expect a 1 billion dollar storage price.

Now let's look at the real numbers:
Video upload speed = 3 * 10^4 minutes per minute.
That's 3 * 10^4 *1440 video footage per day =  4.5 * 10^7 minutes.
Video encoding can reduce a 1-hour film to 1 GB. So 1 million GB is the requirement. That's 1 PB.

So the original cost is similar to what the real numbers say.


If we are off by order of magnitude, it's good. However, being off by 3 or more orders of magnitude is too much. We can then highlight the following:
Where our assumption was wrong, or 
Which factor we didn't take into account.

In the video, I dissected the Google File System research paper from 2003, highlighting its key aspects. The system is designed to run on commodity hardware, making it scalable and fault-tolerant. Google optimized for storing large files, focusing on append operations rather than overwrites. They also emphasized fault detection, fault tolerance, and automated recovery. The system divided files into chunks for parallelism, load balancing, fault tolerance, and easy storage allocation. Replication factor of 3 ensured fault tolerance, with a master node managing metadata.

other_videos.title: How Tesla Became The Most Popular Car Brand In Norway
other_videos.description:
Norway has had massive success with EV adoption, with 82% of new cars sold in the country last year being electric. This high adoption rate can be attributed to the generous subsidies that Norway has offered to electric vehicle owners as well as the country‚Äôs investment in charging infrastructure. Tesla‚Äôs sales in Norway represent only a sliver of the 1.8 million vehicles the company delivered last year, but Norway‚Äôs importance to Tesla goes beyond cold hard cash. Tesla‚Äôs early foothold in the country has made Norway the perfect proving ground for the company and acted as a poster child for the EV transition as a whole. As a result, Tesla CEO, Elon Musk has taken a number of trips to the small Nordic country and has often praised Norway‚Äôs support of electric vehicles. Norwegians were the first European customers to receive deliveries of the Model S in 2013 and it quickly became the country‚Äôs best-selling car. Today, that title has been transferred over to Tesla‚Äôs Model Y. But with competition from other EV cars from automakers including Toyota, Skoda, Volkswagan and BYD heating up, it remains to be seen if Norwegians will continue to choose Tesla in the future. To learn more about Norway‚Äôs success with electric vehicle adoption, check out CNBC‚Äôs documentary: https://youtu.be/R5DbRyeZNRk

other_videos.title: What the Red Sea ship attacks are really about
other_videos.description:
Yemen's Houthis say they're avenging Gaza. But there's a lot more to it.

Help keep Vox free for everybody: http://www.vox.com/give-now 

After the Israel-Hamas war broke out on October 7, 2023, the Houthis, a Yemeni rebel group, began attacking ships passing through the Red Sea. The Houthis pledged to attack any ship in these waters that does business with Israel, to protest Israel‚Äôs war on Gaza and to show solidarity with Palestinians there. But as the attacks have continued, another motive for them has become apparent: strengthening the Houthis‚Äô control of Yemen. 

After a nine-year civil war, the Houthis today control a sizable area in Yemen, with over 70 percent of the Yemeni population within the group‚Äôs territory. The conflict has devastated the country, creating one of the worst humanitarian crises in the world. More than 377,000 Yemenis have been killed ‚Äî by airstrikes from a Saudi-led coalition; landmines and detonations planted by the Houthis; a lack of medical services; and scarcity of food and water due to a naval blockade. And both the Saudi-led coalition and the Houthis have been accused of committing war crimes against Yemenis.

Today, the Houthis are attempting to establish themselves as Yemen's legitimate leaders in the eyes of Yemenis, though they‚Äôve done little to improve the country‚Äôs humanitarian crisis. The Red Sea attacks, which appear to have significant support among the Yemeni people, might be a means to achieve that goal.

Subscribe to our channel and turn on notifications (üîî) so you don't miss any videos: http://goo.gl/0bsAjO

other_videos.title: Volkswagen will bring POLO in some form soon! - Brand Director, Ashish Gupta
other_videos.description:
I had the privilege of conducting an insightful interview with Mr. Ashish Gupta at the highly anticipated VW Annual Brand Conference 2024. During our discussion, we delved into various aspects of Volkswagen's innovative ventures and strategic initiatives.

One highlight of our conversation was the unveiling of Polo, Volkswagen's latest electric vehicle. Mr. Gupta provided valuable insights into the development process, highlighting its significance in the company's commitment to sustainability and technological advancement.

Additionally, we explored Volkswagen's strategic approach to bridging the gap between the Taigun and Tiguan models with a stopgap product, a strategy aimed at meeting diverse consumer needs while maintaining brand cohesion and market competitiveness.

A significant portion of our discussion centered on the growing importance of Advanced Driver Assistance Systems (ADAS) features in today's automotive market, particularly from a sales perspective. Mr. Gupta offered compelling perspectives on how Volkswagen integrates ADAS technologies into their vehicles to enhance safety, convenience, and overall driving experience, thus catering to evolving consumer preferences and regulatory standards.

Furthermore, Mr. Gupta provided valuable insights into Volkswagen's newly launched accessories, shedding light on how these offerings complement the brand's vehicle lineup, enhance customization options, and contribute to the overall ownership experience.

Overall, my conversation with Mr. Ashish Gupta offered a comprehensive understanding of Volkswagen's strategic direction, innovative product portfolio, and commitment to delivering exceptional value to customers in an ever-evolving automotive landscape.

other_videos.title: From Manager To Leader
other_videos.description:
Share this if you think someone else can benefit from this too.

Hey, you know how we've been chatting about work and where we're headed in our careers?

Well, it's got me thinking that I need to talk to you about how to shift from being a manager to becoming a leader.ü§î

After all, that‚Äôs the path forward for someone to grow to the next levels in their careers and own their true potential.

It's like going from playing a small role in a play to directing the entire production.

When you're managing, it's about keeping things ticking over smoothly, right?

But when you step into leadership, it's a whole new level. It's about having this big-picture vision, inspiring others, and driving real change.

And you know what's cool? It's not just about being the boss or having a fancy title. It's about really understanding yourself, your team, and creating an environment where everyone can shine and grow.üíØ

Leaders aren't just people in charge; they're like coaches, cheerleaders, and visionaries rolled into one. They show us that success isn't just about the title (though that‚Äôs awesome too, along with the money) ‚Äì it's about making a meaningful impact and leaving our mark on the world. True potential right there!üôå‚úÖÔ∏è

So, let's think about how we can level up from managing to leading. Who knows what awesome opportunities we'll uncover along the way?

Share this if you think someone else can benefit from this too.

other_videos.title: 9 Mistakes Every Investor Makes | Why People Lose Money In Stock Market?
other_videos.description:
Stock Market: Strategies, Pitfalls, and Solutions

Investing in stocks can be thrilling yet challenging. Many investors face hurdles like timing the market, emotional attachments to companies, and neglecting diversification. Let‚Äôs delve into these pitfalls and ways to overcome them.

Timing the Market:
Trying to predict market movements is risky. Instead, focus on long-term investments. Regular contributions and diversification can help mitigate market volatility.

Not Understanding the Business:
Investing without understanding a company‚Äôs fundamentals is akin to gambling. Thorough research is crucial. Analyze the business model, financials, and industry dynamics before investing.

I Love the Company:
Emotional attachment can cloud judgment. Base investment decisions on objective analysis rather than feelings.

Averaging Down:
Buying more shares as the stock price drops can be tempting, but it can lead to further losses. Reevaluate the investment thesis before averaging down.

Tunnel Vision: My Price, My Portfolio:
Focusing solely on target prices or allocations can lead to missed opportunities. Stay flexible and adapt to changing market conditions.

Looking Only at Stock Price:
Stock prices may not reflect a company‚Äôs true value. Conduct fundamental analysis to assess a company‚Äôs health and prospects.

Penny Stock Speculation:
Investing in penny stocks can be risky due to volatility and speculation. Allocate only a small portion of your portfolio to speculative investments and conduct thorough research.

Allocation Problem:
Proper asset allocation is crucial for managing risk. Diversify across different asset classes and sectors to optimize returns.

Waiting to Get Even: The Biggest Blunder:
Holding onto losing investments indefinitely can hinder portfolio growth. Cut losses and reallocate funds to better opportunities.

How to Mitigate:

Why Are You Even Doing This?: 
Align your investment strategy with your goals, time horizon, and risk tolerance.

Automate: Implement automatic investment plans like dollar-cost averaging to maintain discipline.

Play Part: Stay informed but acknowledge that not every market movement can be predicted. Focus on disciplined, diversified, long-term investing.

In conclusion, understanding common pitfalls and implementing mitigation strategies can help investors navigate the stock market more effectively, increasing their chances of achieving long-term financial success.

other_videos.title: BEST INDEX to invest for 15-20 years? Nifty LargeMidcap 250 Index | Complete Review
other_videos.description:
The Nifty Large Midcap 250 Index offers several advantages over other indices:

Balanced Exposure: It provides a balanced exposure to both large-cap and mid-cap segments, mitigating the risk associated with either segment's performance. This balanced approach ensures that investors benefit from the stability of large-cap stocks while also tapping into the growth potential of mid-cap stocks.

Diversification: By equally allocating investments between large-cap and mid-cap companies, the index fund offers diversification across various companies, sectors, and market capitalizations. This diversification helps spread risk and potentially enhances returns over the long term.

Optimized Allocation: The index fund invests your money equally between the top 100 large companies and the next 150 midcap companies. This allocation strategy is optimized to capture opportunities across both segments of the market, maximizing the potential for returns while minimizing risk.

Historical Performance: Over various time horizons, the Nifty LargeMidcap 250 Index has demonstrated strong performance relative to other indices such as the Nifty 100 Index and the Nifty Midcap 150 Index. It has outperformed the Nifty 100 Index across multiple long-term periods, indicating its ability to generate superior returns over time.

Return-Risk Ratio: The index exhibits a higher return-risk ratio compared to the Nifty 100 Index over both short and long-term horizons. This suggests that investors can potentially achieve higher returns for a given level of risk by investing in the Nifty LargeMidcap 250 Index compared to the Nifty 100 Index.

Overall, the Nifty LargeMidcap 250 Index offers investors a well-rounded investment opportunity, combining the stability of large-cap stocks with the growth potential of mid-cap stocks, along with the benefits of diversification and historical performance.

Historically over a long term this has outperformed Nifty 50 significantly.

other_videos.title: 2X your money in 4 years? | Rule of 72
other_videos.description:
2X your money every 4 years | Rule of 72
The Rule of 72 is an easy-to-use formula designed to estimate the time needed for an investment to double its value, given a specific rate of return. This rule is particularly useful with compounded interest rates and tends to be most accurate for rates between 6% and 10%. Beyond investments, the Rule of 72 can also be applied to other areas experiencing exponential growth, such as GDP or inflation rates. It's helpful in understanding the long-term impacts of annual fees on the growth of investments. Additionally, the Rule of 72 can assist in calculating the rate of return necessary for an investment to double within a set time frame. In various circumstances, alternative rules like the Rule of 69, Rule of 70, or Rule of 73 might offer more precision.

How Do You Calculate the Rule of 72?
The Rule of 72 is a straightforward way to estimate how long it will take for an investment to double in value. Simply divide 72 by the investment's expected annual return rate to get the number of years it will approximately take for your investment to double.

For example, if you have an investment opportunity that promises an 8% annual compounded rate of return, it will take about nine years (72 / 8 = 9) for the investment to double. This means, if you invest ‚Çπ10,000 at this rate, your investment will grow to ‚Çπ20,000 in 9 years, ‚Çπ40,000 in 18 years, ‚Çπ80,000 in 27 years, and so on.

other_videos.title: How Nvidia Grew From Gaming To A.I. Giant, Now Powering ChatGPT
other_videos.description:
Thirty years ago, Taiwan immigrant Jensen Huang founded Nvidia with the dream of revolutionizing PCs and gaming with 3D graphics. In 1999, after laying off the majority of workers and nearly going bankrupt, the company succeeded when it launched what it claims as the world‚Äôs first Graphics Processing Unit (GPU). Then Jensen bet the company on something entirely different: AI. Now, that bet is paying off in a big way as Nvidia‚Äôs A100 chips quickly become the coveted training engines for ChatGPT and other generative AI. But as the chip shortage eases, other chip giants like Intel are struggling. And with all it‚Äôs chips made by TSMC in Taiwan, Nvidia remains vulnerable to mounting U.S.-China trade tensions. We went to Nvidia‚Äôs Silicon Valley, California, headquarters to talk with Huang and get a behind-the scenes-look at the chips powering gaming and the AI boom.

other_videos.title: How to Move from Manager to Leader or Executive Level: 5 Powerful Insights!
other_videos.description:
When you want to move from manager to leader or executive level, there are certain shifts you need to make in your approach to work. Because what got you to a management position, won't get you into a leadership role. You will need to learn new skills, leadership skills, executive level qualities that will help you advance and get promoted into leadership. 

These skills aren't difficult for you to learn, nor should you be intimidated by them. Simply watch this video and I will guide you through the changes you need to make. And remember, it's not always about doing more, sometimes it's about identifying what you need to do less of (I talk more about this in the video). 

So click on the above video and start learning the how to move from manager to leader or executive role. I encourage you to start implementing these skills early while you're still in a management position. That way, you'll be ready for a leadership promotion when it comes along.

other_videos.title: Best Ways to Invest (2025 Edition) | The ULTIMATE INVESTING GUIDE for Beginners
other_videos.description:
Learn Basic Of Stock Market Investments | https://www.financeboosan.in

‚ÄéFollow the Finance Boosan channel on WhatsApp: https://whatsapp.com/channel/0029Va6xVGJ1iUxff71r8p23

Do this before investing

1. Emergency Fund:
   - Purpose: It serves as a financial safety net in unforeseen circumstances like job loss, medical emergencies, or urgent home repairs.
   - How much to save: Generally, it's recommended to have enough to cover 3-6 months of living expenses.
   - Where to keep it: This fund should be easily accessible, ideally in a high-yield savings account or a liquid fund.

2. Term Insurance:
   - What it is: Term insurance is a type of life insurance that provides coverage at a fixed rate of payments for a limited period. 
   - Importance: It's crucial for those with financial dependents to ensure their family‚Äôs financial security in case of the policyholder's untimely demise.

3. Health Insurance:
   - Why it's needed: Health insurance covers medical expenses, which can be financially devastating without coverage.
   - What to consider: Look for a policy with a sufficient cover, considering factors like family health history, coverage for critical illnesses, and network hospitals.

4. Repay Your Debts:
   - Strategy: Prioritize high-interest debts like credit card balances. Consider debt consolidation or refinancing for better interest rates.
   - Importance: Reducing debt lowers financial risk and interest expenses, freeing up more money for investments.

Next, consider your investment strategy based on risk appetite, investment goals, and time horizon. Here are major categories to consider:

1. Fixed or Recurring Deposits:
   - Characteristics: Safe, predictable returns, best for short-term goals.
   - Consideration: Generally offer lower returns compared to other investment types.

2. Mutual Funds:
   - Types: Equity-Linked Savings Scheme (ELSS) for tax-saving, Index Funds for passive investing - Active Funds for high risk appetite individuals.
   - Benefits: Diversification, professional management, suitable for a range of investment goals.

3. Gold:
   - Options: Sovereign Gold Bonds (SGB), Gold Exchange-Traded Funds (ETFs), and Gold Mutual Funds.
   - Role in Portfolio: Acts as a hedge against inflation and market volatility.

4. Bonds:
   - What they are: Debt instruments where an investor loans money to an entity (corporate or governmental) that borrows the funds for a defined period at a fixed interest rate.
   - Risk and Return: Generally safer than stocks but with lower potential returns.

5. Real Estate:
   - Investment in property: Can be for rental income or capital appreciation.
   - Considerations: Requires significant capital, subject to market risks and liquidity concerns.

6. Direct Stocks:
   - What it entails: Buying shares of individual companies.
   - Considerations: High risk and high potential returns, requires market knowledge and active management.

‚ÄéFollow the Finance Boosan channel on WhatsApp: https://whatsapp.com/channel/0029Va6xVGJ1iUxff71r8p23


3x Monthly Income Rule: Aim to save or invest at least three times your monthly income each year. For instance, if you earn 40K per month, you should have saved or invested 1.2L by year-end. This represents a 25% savings rate, which is slightly below the average savings rate in India (30.2%) but still substantial to start with.

5 Day Rule: Invest or save at least 25% of your income within five days of receiving your paycheck. This can be automated through SIPs (Systematic Investment Plans), RDs (Recurring Deposits), or SSYs (Sukanya Samriddhi Yojanas). For those with irregular income, the key is to invest within five days of receiving the majority of your income.

‚Äú3‚Äù before ‚Äú3‚Äù Rule: Prioritize having an emergency fund, term insurance, and health insurance before investing. An emergency fund should be equivalent to three times your monthly expenses and kept in highly liquid forms like a bank FD or savings account.

40% EMI Debt Repayment Rule: Your EMI (Equated Monthly Installment) or debt payments should not exceed 40% of your total income. If your EMIs are too high, the recommendation is to increase your income to keep the EMI within 40% of your income.

16 EMI Rule: To quickly pay off loans, aim to pay 16 EMIs per year instead of the usual 12. This can significantly reduce the total interest paid and the loan period.

25X Rule: Ensure your term insurance coverage is at least 25 times your annual expenses. This amount of coverage ensures sufficient funds for many years, accounting for inflation and lifestyle maintenance.

Rule of 72: This rule helps estimate the time it takes for an investment to double at a given annual rate of return. For example, at a 12% return rate, it would take about 6 years to double the investment.

other_videos.title: How to Get Good at Small Talk, and Even Enjoy It
other_videos.description:
Even if you don‚Äôt think you‚Äôre a natural (or you hate it), anyone can become proficient at this important art using the right tactics and behaviors.

00:00 ‚ÄúSmall talk‚Äù is a misnomer for such an important part of communication.
01:07 Establish appropriate goals.
01:52 Give yourself permission to pause.
03:35 What if you feel like you have nothing smart to say?
04:24 What if I make a mistake or say something dumb?
05:09 What if my problem is that I have too much to say?
06:04 What tools can I use if none of this is natural to me?
07:53 How do I get the conversation started?
09:00 How do I end the conversation (gracefully)?

According to Matt Abrahams, author of "Think Faster, Talk Smarter: How to Speak Successfully When You're Put on the Spot", key strategies include avoiding conventional responses in favor of establishing genuine connections, prioritizing brevity while delivering messages, and speaking authentically without the pressure to be perfect‚Äîwhich means daring to be dull. Fear or nervousness need not deter anyone from communicating effectively on the spot.

Read more: https://hbr.org/2023/09/how-to-shine-when-youre-put-on-the-spot

And there's more by Matt Abrahams on this topic in his new book: https://www.amazon.com/Think-Faster-Talk-Smarter-Successfully/dp/1668010305/

other_videos.description:
President Xi Jinping‚Äôs November meeting with President Joe Biden at the APEC summit in San Francisco came amid simmering tensions between China and the US. Technology has been at the heart of those strains, particularly Washington‚Äôs efforts to restrict Chinese access to key semiconductor innovations.

Huawei‚Äôs August unveiling of a new smartphone was a blow to America. The Mate 60 Pro appeared to be more advanced than should have been possible, given import controls imposed by the US Department of Commerce. Bloomberg commissioned the first teardown of the handset, by the analysis firm TechInsights. The findings raised questions about the effectiveness of the US-led controls.

other_videos.description:
The Stuntman becomes the hero. #TheFallGuyMovie only in theaters May 3.

------

He‚Äôs a stuntman, and like everyone in the stunt community, he gets blown up, shot, crashed, thrown through windows and dropped from the highest of heights, all for our entertainment. And now, fresh off an almost career-ending accident, this working-class hero has to track down a missing movie star, solve a conspiracy and try to win back the love of his life while still doing his day job. What could possibly go right? 

From real life stunt man and director David Leitch, the blockbuster director of Bullet Train, Deadpool 2, Atomic Blonde and Fast & Furious Presents: Hobbs & Shaw and the producer of John Wick, Nobody and Violent Night, comes his most personal film yet. A new hilarious, hard-driving, all-star apex-action thriller and love letter to action movies and the hard-working and under-appreciated crew of people who make them: The Fall Guy. 

Oscar¬Æ nominee Ryan Gosling (Barbie, La La Land, Drive) stars as Colt Seavers, a battle-scarred stuntman who, having left the business a year earlier to focus on both his physical and mental health, is drafted back into service when the star of a mega-budget studio movie‚Äîbeing directed by his ex, Jody Moreno, played by Golden Globe winner Emily Blunt (Oppenheimer, A Quiet Place films, Sicario)‚Äîgoes missing.

While the film‚Äôs ruthless producer (Emmy winner Hannah Waddingham; Ted Lasso), maneuvers to keep the disappearance of star Tom Ryder (Golden Globe winner Aaron Taylor-Johnson; Bullet Train) a secret from the studio and the media, Colt performs the film‚Äôs most outrageous stunts while trying (with limited success) to charm his way back into Jody‚Äôs good graces. But as the mystery around the missing star deepens, Colt will find himself ensnared in a sinister, criminal plot that will push him to the edge of a fall more dangerous than any stunt.

Inspired by the hit 1980s TV series, The Fall Guy also stars Winston Duke (Black Panther franchise) and Academy Award¬Æ nominee Stephanie Hsu (Everything Everywhere All at Once). 

From a screenplay by Hobbs & Shaw screenwriter Drew Pearce, The Fall Guy is produced by Kelly McCormick (Bullet Train, Nobody, Atomic Blonde) and David Leitch for their company 87North, and by Ryan Gosling and by Guymon Casady (Game of Thrones, Steve Jobs and executive producer of the upcoming series Ripley) for Entertainment 360. The film is executive produced by Drew Pearce, Entertainment 360‚Äôs Geoff Shaevitz and the creator of the original Fall Guy television series, Glen A. Larson.

other_videos.title: Productivity Guilt   #SHORTS
other_videos.description:
PRODUCTIVITY GUILT‚Ä¶‚Å£    #SHORTS
That continual nagging feeling that you haven‚Äôt done enough‚Ä¶ That you‚Äôre so far behind‚Ä¶ That you can‚Äôt take a break because you don‚Äôt deserve it‚Ä¶‚Å£
‚Å£
Sound familiar? ü§∑üèª‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è‚Å£
‚Å£
It‚Äôs quite common among high achievers, and could also a ‚Äòsymptom‚Äô of imposter syndrome and high functioning anxiety.‚Å£
‚Å£
If this is something you experience (It is for me!) here are 3 suggestions that might help;‚Å£
‚Å£
1Ô∏è‚É£ Accept You‚Äôll Always Be Imperfect‚Å£
‚Å£
Perfection isn‚Äôt the standard you want to be aiming for‚Ä¶ Instead, strive for ‚Äòhuman‚Äô. What does that mean? Well, you can have high standards and strive for excellence, but also know that you‚Äôre only human and only have so much you can fit in your mind (‚Äòcognitive load‚Äô) 7 into your life. And guess what‚Ä¶ mistakes come with the territory!‚Å£
‚Å£
2Ô∏è‚É£ Don‚Äôt focus on the Gap between Current Self & Ideal Self‚Å£
‚Å£
One of the reasons why you feel this ‚Äòguilt‚Äô is that you‚Äôre not where you want to be. You have this vision of your ‚Äòideal‚Äô self which is more disciplined, more successful, more of who you want to be‚Ä¶ and you become fixated on the giant gap between this state and where you actually are. Instead of looking at the gap, focus on what you‚Äôre doing each day to take one small step closer to the goal state.‚Å£
‚Å£
3Ô∏è‚É£ Prioritize rest‚Å£
‚Å£
One big mistake you might be making if you‚Äôve fallen into the trap of productivity guilt is that you keep pushing to the point of diminishing returns. You‚Äôre no longer ‚Äòproductive‚Äô, but you don‚Äôt stop (‚Äòhello guilt!‚Äô). ‚Å£

From the twisted mind of Matthew Vaughn (Kingsman franchise, Kick-Ass) comes Argylle, a razor-witted, reality-bending, globe-encircling spy thriller.
 
Bryce Dallas Howard (Jurassic World franchise) is Elly Conway, the reclusive author of a series of best-selling espionage novels, whose idea of bliss is a night at home with her computer and her cat, Alfie. But when the plots of Elly‚Äôs fictional books‚Äîwhich center on secret agent Argylle and his mission to unravel a global spy syndicate‚Äîbegin to mirror the covert actions of a real-life spy organization, quiet evenings at home become a thing of the past.
 
Accompanied by Aiden (Oscar¬Æ winner Sam Rockwell), a cat-allergic spy, Elly (carrying Alfie in her backpack) races across the world to stay one step ahead of the killers as the line between Elly‚Äôs fictional world and her real one begins to blur.
 
The top-flight ensemble cast features Henry Cavill (The Witcher), John Cena (Fast X), Oscar¬Æ winner Ariana DeBose (West Side Story), Grammy winning pop superstar Dua Lipa (Barbie), Emmy winner and Oscar¬Æ nominee Bryan Cranston (Breaking Bad), Emmy winner and comedy icon Catherine O‚ÄôHara (Schitt‚Äôs Creek), Sofia Boutella (Kingsman: The Secret Service), and the legendary Samuel L. Jackson. Alfie is played by Chip, the real-life cat of supermodel Claudia Vaughn (n√©e Schiffer).

other_videos.title: Gallagher Explains Pronunciation | Stand-Up | The New Smothers Brothers Comedy Hour
other_videos.description:
Gallagher performs hilarious stand-up comedy on The New Smothers Brothers Comedy Hour.

The Smothers Brothers, Tom and Dick, are one of the most iconic comedy duos in the history of television. Tom and Dick began performing as a duo in the late 1950s, playing in coffeehouses and clubs in San Francisco. Their act consisted of music, comedy, and witty banter, which quickly gained them a following.

The Smothers Brothers became a household name in the late 1960s with their variety show, The Smothers Brothers Comedy Hour. The show was groundbreaking in its approach to comedy, pushing the boundaries with political satire and social commentary. The show also featured up-and-coming musical acts, including The Doors and The Who, and introduced the world to comedians like Steve Martin and George Carlin.

The Smothers Brothers' irreverent style has made them a beloved and enduring force in American comedy.

other_videos.title: BLUE BEETLE | OFFICIAL FINAL TRAILER
other_videos.description:
The Reyes family just got its first superhero.  #BlueBeetle - Only in theaters August 18.

From Warner Bros. Pictures comes the feature film ‚ÄúBlue Beetle,‚Äù marking the DC Super Hero‚Äôs first time on the big screen. The film, directed by Angel Manuel Soto, stars Xolo Maridue√±a in the title role as well as his alter ego, Jaime Reyes.

Recent college grad Jaime Reyes returns home full of aspirations for his future, only to find that home is not quite as he left it. As he searches to find his purpose in the world, fate intervenes when Jaime unexpectedly finds himself in possession of an ancient relic of alien biotechnology: the Scarab. When the Scarab suddenly chooses Jaime to be its symbiotic host, he is bestowed with an incredible suit of armor capable of extraordinary and unpredictable powers, forever changing his destiny as he becomes the Super Hero BLUE BEETLE.

Starring alongside Maridue√±a (‚ÄúCobra Kai‚Äù) are Adriana Barraza (‚ÄúRambo: Last Blood,‚Äù ‚ÄúThor‚Äù), Dam√≠an Alc√°zar (‚ÄúNarcos,‚Äù ‚ÄúNarcos: Mexico‚Äù), Elpidia Carrillo (‚ÄúMayans M.C.,‚Äù the ‚ÄúPredator‚Äù films), Bruna Marquezine (‚ÄúMaldivas,‚Äù ‚ÄúGod Save the King‚Äù), Raoul Max Trujillo (the ‚ÄúSicario‚Äù films, ‚ÄúMayans M.C.‚Äù), with Oscar winner Susan Sarandon (‚ÄúMonarch,‚Äù ‚ÄúDead Man Walking‚Äù), and George Lopez (the ‚ÄúRio and ‚ÄúSmurf‚Äù franchises). The film also stars Belissa Escobedo (‚ÄúAmerican Horror Stories,‚Äù ‚ÄúHocus Pocus 2‚Äù) and Harvey Guill√©n (‚ÄúWhat We Do in the Shadows‚Äù). Soto (‚ÄúCharm City Kings,‚Äù ‚ÄúThe Farm‚Äù) directs from a screenplay by Gareth Dunnet-Alcocer (‚ÄúMiss Bala‚Äù), based on characters from DC. John Rickard and Zev Foreman are producing, with Walter Hamada, Galen Vaisman and Garrett Grant serving as executive producers.

The director‚Äôs creative team behind the scenes includes director of photography Pawel Pogorzelski (‚ÄúMidsommar,‚Äù ‚ÄúHereditary‚Äù), production designer John Billington (‚ÄúBad Boys for Life‚Äù), editor Craig Alpert (‚ÄúDeadpool 2,‚Äù ‚ÄúThe Lost City‚Äù), Oscar-nominated costume designer Mayes C. Rubeo (‚ÄúJojo Rabbit,‚Äù the ‚ÄúThor‚Äù films), visual effects supervisor Kelvin McIlwain (‚ÄúThe Suicide Squad,‚Äù ‚ÄúAquaman‚Äù) and composer Bobby Krlic (‚ÄúMidsommar,‚Äù the ‚ÄúSnowpiercer‚Äù series).

A Warner Bros. Pictures Presentation, a Safran Company Production, ‚ÄúBlue Beetle‚Äù soars into theaters only internationally beginning August 2023 and in North America August 18, 2023. It will be distributed worldwide by Warner Bros. Pictures.

other_videos.description:
Amazon India's Secret Plan üòÆ

Amazon came to India in 2013 and since then they have invested $6 Billion in the country.

They want to increase this investment to $26 Billion by 2030.

But what's surprising is, Amazon's E-commerce business in India hasn't made a single rupee in profit in the last ten years.

Amazon is actually so much bullish on India because of the growth of cloud computing in India and they are the market leader here.

Google and Microsoft are far lagging behind in this race.

other_videos.title: Why Google picked Gujarat? üòÆ
other_videos.description:
Why Google picked Gujarat? üòÆ

Google's first global fintech center is going to be set up in GIFT City, Gujarat.

CEO Sundar Pichai spoke to PM Modi regarding this recently.

Google will use this center to manage its global fintech products like Google Pay, which is already the second-largest UPI payments app in India.

Google is pretty impressed with what India has done in the digital infrastructure space with things like Aadhar and UPI and it wants to use this to build its future products.

And it chose Gujarat because of GIFT City, a special economic zone near Ahmedabad, which the Indian government is trying to push as a global financial center.

Google setting up its only global fintech center in the country shows India‚Äôs growing prominence in the fintech landscape.

The end of the road begins. 

Fast X, the tenth film in the Fast & Furious Saga, launches the final chapters of one of cinema‚Äôs most storied and popular global franchises, now in its third decade and still going strong with the same core cast and characters as when it began.

Over many missions and against impossible odds, Dom Toretto (Vin Diesel) and his family have outsmarted, out-nerved and outdriven every foe in their path. Now, they confront the most lethal opponent they‚Äôve ever faced: A terrifying threat emerging from the shadows of the past who‚Äôs fueled by blood revenge, and who is determined to shatter this family and destroy everything‚Äîand everyone‚Äîthat Dom loves, forever.  
 
In 2011‚Äôs Fast Five, Dom and his crew took out nefarious Brazilian drug kingpin Hernan Reyes and decapitated his empire on a bridge in Rio De Janeiro. What they didn‚Äôt know was that Reyes‚Äô son, Dante (Aquaman‚Äôs Jason Momoa), witnessed it all and has spent the last 12 years masterminding a plan to make Dom pay the ultimate price. 
 
Dante‚Äôs plot will scatter Dom‚Äôs family from Los Angeles to the catacombs of Rome, from Brazil to London and from Portugal to Antarctica. New allies will be forged and old enemies will resurface. But everything changes when Dom discovers that his own 8-year-old son (Leo Abelo Perry, Black-ish) is the ultimate target of Dante‚Äôs vengeance. 
 
Directed by Louis Leterrier (Clash of the Titans, The Incredible Hulk), Fast X stars returning cast members Michelle Rodriguez, Tyrese Gibson, Chris ‚ÄúLudacris‚Äù Bridges, Nathalie Emmanuel, Jordana Brewster, Sung Kang, Jason Statham, John Cena and Scott Eastwood, with Oscar¬Æ winner Helen Mirren and Oscar¬Æ winner Charlize Theron. 
 
The film also features an extraordinary new cast including Oscar¬Æ winner Brie Larson as Tess, a rogue representative from the Agency; Alan Richtson (Reacher) as Aimes, the new head of the Agency who doesn‚Äôt hold the same fondness for Dom‚Äôs crew as his predecessor, Mr. Nobody; Daniela Melchior (The Suicide Squad) as a Brazilian street racer with a powerful tie to Dom‚Äôs past; and legendary Oscar¬Æ winner Rita Moreno as Dom and Mia‚Äôs Abuelita Toretto. 
 
Fast X is produced by Neal H. Moritz, Vin Diesel, Justin Lin, Jeff Kirschenbaum and Samantha Vincent. The executive producers are Joseph M. Caracciolo, Jr., David Cain, Chris Morgan, Amanda Lewis and Mark Bomback. www.thefastsaga.com

other_videos.title: Risks of Large Language Models (LLM)
other_videos.description:
Learn about watsonx ‚Üí https://ibm.biz/BdvxRe

With all the excitement around chatGPT, it‚Äôs easy to lose sight of the unique risks of generative AI. Large language models (LLMs) -- a form of generative AI -- are really good at creating prose that sounds like a native speaker.  But because they‚Äôre so good at it, large language models may give a false impression they possess actual understanding. They don't! In this video, Phaedra Boinodiris explains the potential risks of relying on large language models to your business, brand, or even society. She also presents mitigation strategies for reducing these risks.

#watsonx #llm #llms

other_videos.title: The Flash ‚Äì Official Trailer
other_videos.description:
On June 16, worlds collide. Watch the official trailer now for The Flash ‚Äì only in theaters. #TheFlashMovie 

Warner Bros. Pictures presents ‚ÄúThe Flash,‚Äù directed by Andy Muschietti (the ‚ÄúIT‚Äù films, ‚ÄúMama‚Äù). Ezra Miller reprises their role as Barry Allen in the DC Super Hero‚Äôs first-ever standalone feature film.

Worlds collide in ‚ÄúThe Flash‚Äù when Barry uses his superpowers to travel back in time in order to change the events of the past. But when his attempt to save his family inadvertently alters the future, Barry becomes trapped in a reality in which General Zod has returned, threatening annihilation, and there are no Super Heroes to turn to. That is, unless Barry can coax a very different Batman out of retirement and rescue an imprisoned Kryptonian‚Ä¶ albeit not the one he‚Äôs looking for. Ultimately, to save the world that he is in and return to the future that he knows, Barry‚Äôs only hope is to race for his life. But will making the ultimate sacrifice be enough to reset the universe? 

‚ÄúThe Flash‚Äù ensemble also includes rising star Sasha Calle, Michael Shannon (‚ÄúBullet Train,‚Äù ‚ÄúBatman v Superman: Dawn of Justice‚Äù), Ron Livingston (‚ÄúLoudermilk,‚Äù ‚ÄúThe Conjuring‚Äù), Maribel Verd√∫ (‚ÄúElite,‚Äù ‚ÄúY tu mam√° tambi√©n‚Äù), Kiersey Clemons (‚ÄúZack Snyder‚Äôs Justice League,‚Äù ‚ÄúSweetheart‚Äù), Antje Traue (‚ÄúKing of Ravens,‚Äù ‚ÄúMan of Steel‚Äù) and Michael Keaton (‚ÄúSpider-Man: Homecoming,‚Äù ‚ÄúBatman‚Äù).

‚ÄúThe Flash‚Äù is produced by Barbara Muschietti (the ‚ÄúIT‚Äù films, ‚ÄúMama‚Äù) and Michael Disco (‚ÄúRampage,‚Äù ‚ÄúSan Andreas‚Äù). The screenplay is by Christina Hodson (‚ÄúBirds of Prey,‚Äù ‚ÄúBumblebee‚Äù), with a screen story by John Francis Daley & Jonathan Goldstein (‚ÄúDungeons & Dragons: Honor Among Thieves,‚Äù ‚ÄúSpider-Man: Homecoming‚Äù) and Joby Harold (‚ÄúTransformers: Rise of the Beasts,‚Äù ‚ÄúArmy of the Dead‚Äù), based on characters from DC. The executive producers 
are Toby Emmerich, Walter Hamada, Galen Vaisman and Marianne Jenkins.

Joining director Muschietti behind the camera are director of photography Henry Braham (‚ÄúGuardians of the Galaxy Vol. 3,‚Äù ‚ÄúThe Suicide Squad‚Äù), production designer Paul Denham Austerberry (‚ÄúIT Chapter Two,‚Äù ‚ÄúThe Shape of Water‚Äù), editors Jason Ballantine (the ‚ÄúIT‚Äù films, ‚ÄúThe Great Gatsby‚Äù) and Paul Machliss (‚ÄúThe Gentlemen,‚Äù ‚ÄúBaby Driver‚Äù), and costume designer Alexandra Byrne (‚ÄúDoctor Strange,‚Äù ‚ÄúGuardians of the Galaxy‚Äù); the score is by Benjamin Wallfisch 
(‚ÄúThe Invisible Man,‚Äù the ‚ÄúIT‚Äù films).

Warner Bros. Pictures presents a Double Dream/a Disco Factory production of an Andy Muschietti film, ‚ÄúThe Flash.‚Äù It will be distributed worldwide by Warner Bros. Pictures and is set to open in theaters in North America on June 16, 2023 and internationally beginning 14 June 2023.
